{"id": "1072", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "A simple solution to all of the hype about calling cells which is by far the most common means of contacting a consumer these days.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "Direct that all telecommunication companies offer a site that allows the agencies to register their phone numbers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "If a call is placed to a consumer that does not have unlimited calling or testing then the charges are reversed to the registered phone agency.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "309", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I do not believe that it is \"just\" to allow a third party to buy a past due debt and sue for the entire balance, plus attorney fees, court costs, and other fees associated with \"mediators or arbitrators\".", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "I believe that a third party debt buyer should be limited as to how much they can sue for above their initial investment.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "Too many times the original creditor is a publically traded company ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "and the loss has already been taken by the share holders.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "Then some debt buyer buys a portfolio of un-performing debt and pays a dime on a dollar for it.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "Sends all of it to a \"law office\" to collect 100% or more of the original alleged obligation.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "The debt buyer should not be able to sue for 900% of their investment.", "reasons": ["8"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "policy", "text": "They should be limited to a percentage of true damage.", "reasons": ["8"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "I know of no other civil process where this would be considered ethical.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "605", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Collection Agency's' should be REQUIRED by law to show their phone number when calling a debtor.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "Most if not all come up \"unknown\".", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "If they are a legitimate company then they should have no problem showing their number.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "If I call them, and my number is blocked, I can't get thru until I unblock my number.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "If they truly are legitimate, they should want to do things fair and above board.", "reasons": ["2", "3"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1408", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "Because credit card contracts are adhesion contracts,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "it is up to educated third party observers to make sure the adhesion contract is fair.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "If a person experiences a dramatic event beyond their control that reduces their income, it seems questionable to not allow the debtor the right to suspend the interest rate charges, penalties and fees until they have regained their income.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "They are still promising to pay,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "but since their life has been turned upside down by an event beyond their control, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "that should have standing in some cases.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "It just doesn't seem ethical to punish a consumer ", "reasons": ["7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "because their home washes down the river one day, or is burned to the ground by a wild fire, destroyed in an earthquake, and so on.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "It especially does not seem ethical that the credit card companies are allowed to hide how they will punish a consumer if the consumer's intent was always to make their payments and it took an act of God to prevent that from happening.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "Insurance policies do not cover acts of war, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "fact", "text": "yet our own government allowed the owner of the twin towers to collect on their insurance policy ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "even though 911 was clearly an act of war.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "fact", "text": "I believe there have been polls that show a majority of americans are upset because the 2008 bailouts did not give them any respite of any kind.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "value", "text": "The \"Promise to Pay\" says nothing about making that payment every month above and beyond all other situations and scenarios.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "value", "text": "I believe judges have misinterpreted Promise to Pay and that lawyers like the way it is set up now ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 15, "type": "value", "text": "so they don't want to challenge the obvious holes in credit card adhesion contracts", "reasons": ["14", "16"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 16, "type": "value", "text": "because it could quash their own future income stream.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1191", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "My only concern about this excellent comment is that consumers not be subjected to a flood of confusing or potentially intimidating information.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "The most useful information is the what, when, who, and why of the original transaction that incurred the unpaid debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "The original creditor should be identified by a name known to the consumer, e.g. DR. JOHN SMITH, RHEUMATOLOGIST not DYNAMIC HEALTHCARE OF GREATER ANYTOWN d/b/a ASSOCIATED SPECIALISTS P.C.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "You get the idea.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1111", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Once the consumer is located then nearbys, neighbors, relatives, prior used phone numbers may be abused by collectors to harass and embarrass consumers, or even to compel a relative or other third party to pay the debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "Violations of the FDCPA should be treated as serious breaches of law.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "591", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "The enforcement mechanism of the FDCPA is laughable from the point of view of the debtor.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "For example, a debt collector said that since they are out of the country they are not required to adhere to the FDCPA.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "Luckily, I knew better, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "but most folk don't.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "The CFPB's voluntary reporting combined with proxy enforcement power may curb the industry's activities, and may be cheaper and faster than class action lawsuits.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1069", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Filing suit in the state that the consumer lives in is the most practical.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "If a state has a large district there is nothing that can be done unless judges want to allow tele-conferencing,, or phone conferencing.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "However, if that is allowed it should be allowed for both sides provided the evidence of the debt is supplied to the court in advance.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "673", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Please include calls to family and friends of debtor.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "We are called frequently to pass on messages for people that have our last name, some of them we don't know.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1243", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I believe that some collection agencies attempt to coerce payment in order to reset the clock on debts that would otherwise be time-barred.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "The real issue here however is one of proper record keeping.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "The collection agencies may not be fully sure if the debt is time barred or not ", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "simply because it has passed hands several times.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "A transcript or log should be available to consumers upon request (at a minimum) showing when, where and who held the collection.", "reasons": ["1", "2"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "403", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Depends on the type of Bankruptcy.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "If it is a CH 13 many times the creditors receive more money than if they choose to forgive a portion of the debt and settle direct with the consumer.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "This is because of the strict \"means test\" for CH 7.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "870", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "we are bombarded with robo calls every day from early am to late evening with unidentified callers;", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "no msgs left after answering machine kicks in;", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "these types of calls should be barred unless msg left with identity of caller included and basis of call to include name of creditor and debtor included", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "198", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "In many districts where bad check diversion programs exist, there is anecdotal evidence that the companies administering the programs threaten with prosecution individuals who do not come within the state's bad check law", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "for example, checks that bounce due to printing errors, checks for which there were funds available when written but not when presented, and individuals who pay the amount due by other means within grace periods permitted by state law.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "The CFPB should ensure that bad check diversion programs have a realistic means of ensuring that only individuals realistically subject to prosecution are targeted,", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "and should also require that, in order to qualify for the 1692p safe harbor, diversion programs prohibit misleading communications and misstatements of state bad check law.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "234", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "They can't be sued on in court ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "and communications should reflect that.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have found that persons who buy old debts are not competent and rely on software and letter services to fulfill their collection obligations.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Perhaps it is time to return to licensing of collectors.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1267", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I am currently going through a miserable experience with a creditor and debt collector.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "In 2004 I completed my college education and consolidated all of my student loans through Nelnet.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "In 2005 (or so) I started to get calls from debt collectors stating that I was delinquent on my loan repayment.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "I explained the situation, that I had made all of my timely payments through Nelnet and, before I would pay anything else, I would need to see some proof of the debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "I never received any proof of the debt ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "and this conversation reoccurred several times for the next five years.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "In 2011 I wanted to buy my (wife\"s) dream home.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "It was a significant purchase ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "testimony", "text": "and the bankers I talked with indicated I needed to clear up the student loan issue to be approved.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "testimony", "text": "I reached out to the original creditor and the debt collector and begged for some proof of the loan.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "testimony", "text": "They then provided me with a loan application (nothing to indicate that the application was approved or that any funds were ever dispersed to me).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "While I was not comfortable with the proof, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "value", "text": "I knew that fighting it out in court would take longer than I was willing to take.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "value", "text": "So, I was very purposeful in my conversations with the original creditor and the debt collector to make sure that the issue would be cleared on my credit report if I paid the full value of the (alleged) loan.", "reasons": ["12"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "testimony", "text": "I also recorded the conversations I had with the original creditor and the debt collector.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 15, "type": "testimony", "text": "I paid the original loan amount ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 16, "type": "testimony", "text": "and (if you didn't see this coming) the original creditor refused to update my credit report.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 17, "type": "testimony", "text": "And, even after providing the credit reporting agencies with proof that the debt was paid, they also refused to update my credit report.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 18, "type": "testimony", "text": "To make matters worse, after the debt was paid, I received a notice from the debt collector that several thousands of dollars had been excused.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 19, "type": "testimony", "text": "I immediately contacted the debt collector and requested documentation that would support their amount due, including documentation where I agreed to a specific interest rate.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 20, "type": "testimony", "text": "No response from the debt collector.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 21, "type": "testimony", "text": "So, I am now arguing it out with the IRS regarding any additional taxes that may be due.", "reasons": ["19_20"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 22, "type": "testimony", "text": "And, even though I paid the debt two years ago, my credit report has not yet been updated.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 23, "type": "value", "text": "It is simply ridiculous than any business would have this much power to have such a negative impact on an individual without any documentation to back it up.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 24, "type": "policy", "text": "Any creditor should be required to provide certain documentation prior to making a negative credit reporting and there should be significant consequences for any creditor/debt collector that pursues a debt without having the required documentation.", "reasons": ["23"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1275", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "One theme we see throughout comments is that debt sold adds confusion as to whom is the creditor, and also triggers a new credit entry, making the debt appear as incremental (additional), when it is simply transferred, and fresh.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "The solution to this is simple; ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "do not allow credit bureaus to ever list more than one entry for the same debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "Put the burden of accurate recordkeeping on the bureaus, ", "reasons": ["4", "5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "because they are the only entities who have a responsibility for accurate recordkeeping ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "and they are paid to keep accurate records.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "Currently the cost of sloppy systems is externalized to both creditors and borrowers, both of whom tend to re-externalize it to other creditors and borrowers in the form of higher costs.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "It is irrelevant whether these dual entries are caused by negligence, incompetence, or malice on the part of the creditor or collector ", "reasons": ["8"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "because it is the responsibility of the credit reporting agency to make this practice impossible.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "Adding steep fines for double reporting would incentivize CRA's to police their systems so each debt only garners one entry.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "fact", "text": "Since CRA's are immune from libel suits in most of the country ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "regulatory oversight is especially important.", "reasons": ["10"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "value", "text": "Conversely, clarifying that reporting agencies are not immune from state libel laws -- that regulatory authority is in addition to state defamation law -- would also quickly incentivize more accurate reporting.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1403", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Get a copy of the police report ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "and mail it to all three.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "They HAVE to put a freeze on your report, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "and you get a pin, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "and if you have to lift it you need to have that pin.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "It is quite a pain.", "reasons": ["7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "I had a burglary in 2012 -- 14 pages of items stolen, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "I had to call all my credit cards and get issued new ones.", "reasons": ["6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "Heartbreaking --not just things like my computer, but items of great value, and great sentimental value.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "The least you should have is the peace of mind of having a freeze on your report.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "And they HAVE to do it.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "policy", "text": "Otherwise, go to a lawyer and let them dangle on the end of the meat hook.", "reasons": ["12"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "value", "text": "It is a pain, but worth doing.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "389", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Having gone through a Chapter 7 bankruptcy I can tell you that debt collector phone calls were the worst part of the bankruptcy experience.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Massachusetts has it right limiting the number of calls debt collectors can make.", "reasons": ["2", "3", "4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "That would remove one of the favorite illegal tactics debt collectors use to harass debtors.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "Some debt collectors would threaten to put us on robocalls so that our phone rang hourly until we agreed to a repayment loan schedule.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "Or they would threaten to call my spouse at work to see if he would be \"more cooperative\" and agree to a loan repayment schedule even after being informed that his workplace did not allow debt collection calls.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "Nothing phased these people ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "and they appeared to enjoy verbally abusing me.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "Informing them that we wanted all debt collection to be written was also ignored.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "testimony", "text": "I could accurately predict who was calling by the day and time of the calls.", "reasons": ["10", "11", "9"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "testimony", "text": "Chase Bank called every Tuesday morning at 9AM.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "testimony", "text": "Bank of America called every Monday morning at 10:30AM.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "These calls were always professional and appreciated.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "testimony", "text": "I followed specific instructions given by our bankruptcy attorney who did not want the debt collectors to know that we were planning on filing bankruptcy in a few months.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "testimony", "text": "So I faithfully answered every single debt collector call for almost six months.", "reasons": ["12"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "testimony", "text": "I politely confirmed my identity.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 15, "type": "testimony", "text": "I confirmed I owed the debt ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 16, "type": "testimony", "text": "and then I politely told each call that I could not start to repay the debt at this time.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 17, "type": "testimony", "text": "The banks/credit cards accepted this without a problem and remained professional.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 18, "type": "testimony", "text": "Others like GE Capital and the vacation time share debt collectors would then start with the abusive comments.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 19, "type": "testimony", "text": "Calling me a \"deadbeat\" and swearing at me was popular.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 20, "type": "testimony", "text": "Another popular threat was how they would harass us nonstop until they got their money.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 21, "type": "testimony", "text": "What finally put a stop to the unethical tactics was when they would call and inform me that I was being taped I then informed them that I too was now taping their phone calls.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 22, "type": "testimony", "text": "Most immediately hung up.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 23, "type": "testimony", "text": "A few would clean up their act and then act in a professional manner.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 24, "type": "value", "text": "The ability to tape debt collection calls is a powerful tool for the debtor to have", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 25, "type": "value", "text": "and I would encourage this agency to grant debtors this right.", "reasons": ["24", "26"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 26, "type": "value", "text": "Nothing cleaned up the bad behavior like knowing they were being taped.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "774", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Disputes are not investigated.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "That is a joke.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Sending out a letter to whoever these debt collectors think is responsible for the debt is just rote -- it is not done in good faith or follow the letter of the law.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "They 1) use vague names, no signature, post office boxes, a million aliases for their debt collection business", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "THAT practice has to stop).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "The FTC says \"reasonable\" investigation but these companies do none,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "fact", "text": "and that is the standard practice.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "A good start is having a realistic and fair and honest laws requiring the companies to verify debt without already having assumptions or worse, not caring if they have the right person or not.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "policy", "text": "Any rule change needs to carry some penalty", "reasons": ["9"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "or it won't have any impact on an industry that has run roughshod over consumers now for two decades.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "Abuses abound.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "policy", "text": "There also should be special requirements for validating medical debt because of privacy rights.", "reasons": ["12"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "value", "text": "There seems to be no concern of violating people's privacy when it comes to medical debt collection activities.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "442", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "We live in the Information Age.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "All the information this individual is requesting is readily available with a few keystrokes.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "608", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Agreed.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "And it should be their real phone number.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "So that when you miss their phone call and try to call them back, it should go to the real company.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "And not say something like \"the call can not be completed as dialed.\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "I mean, what is the point in that.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "Some debtors can't get to their phone before it goes to the answering machine ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "and if the collectors don't leave a message, the debtor will try to call back.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "But then the call can't be completed when you try to call back.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "So, really what was the point of the call.", "reasons": ["7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "Many debtors would just assume it was a scam call.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "policy", "text": "Increasing Right Party Contacts should be the goal.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "fact", "text": "And that goal can only be reached if the real phone number is showing up on calller id.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "566", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Repeated phone calls are torture.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "There is NO need for this when there is a mail system.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "One completed phone call should be enough.", "reasons": ["0", "1"], "evidence": null}]}
