{"id": "614", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I don't like #2", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "because if they were to start telling consumers to a to a certain website, that opens the door for spammers/hackers to increase virus infections by simply doing the same thing.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Just calling every phone number in the phone book and telling the consumer navigate to a certain website and then infect their computer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "662", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I generally prefer e-mail to telephone communication,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "but you can't be sure the e-mail has reached the person.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "I would suggest a notice that says, \"If you don't acknowledge receipt of this e-mail, we'll start phoning you.\"", "reasons": ["0_1"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "491", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "A standard first letter would be an excellent idea - especially if states would agree on the content.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "Consumers could recognize the format and know where to look for the information they need.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Consumer testing would be a very good idea.", "reasons": ["3", "4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "I believe that industry members would favor this to reduce litigation over technical violations.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "Taxpayers would benefit by reduced federal court expenses.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1193", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I still stand by what I said;", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "CFPB should have a large core of undercover agents with arresting powers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "567", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have experienced a debt collector call me several times in a day although they have already got the voice mail.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "Even if I already have spoke to them and told them my situation and created a \"payment date,\" they call again the next day.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "I do not know if the system is talking to each other or they just have that \"auto dialer\" on and just calls all day and every day.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "It is abusive and on hte verge of harrassment.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "Not to mention, the time that they call is 10pm or 9pm.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "I believe that is too late to call", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "and there should be reasonable time to call and based upon the time zone you LIVE IN not based on the area code of your mobile phone number.", "reasons": ["4_5"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "433", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Once a debt has reached the end of its statue of limitations is should be removed from the consumer credit report.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "However, collectors use the law to refresh old debts so they effectively never leave a report.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "If a collector can't sue to retrieve the debt it has no business on a consumer report.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1410", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Even when the right person is hauled into court, everything From_ill_annoy stated is still true.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "Defaulters should not be forced to complete the same type of court papers that those accused of crimes are required to fill out and file.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "Since debt collection is not considered a criminal act, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "filing papers should be much much easier for the defendant, ", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "and, a defendant should be allowed to plead Involuntary Default and get a better result. such as the freezing of all interest rate charges, penalties and fees in exchange for the promise to pay, even if it takes ten years.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1000", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "A credit reporting agency should be required to immediately comply with information regarding disputed debt and completely remove any reference to the debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "As an example, I am attempting to have a time barred paid lien removed from my Credit Report.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "2 of the 3 bureaus immediately removed, 1 refuses to remove.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have sent documentation from the court, the original creditor, from the office of probate judge all to no avail.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "Without a remedy, I am left with a false item on my credit report.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "997", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Calls at work are too instrusive.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "Most companies, like mine, do not allow personal calls.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "Not all people have M-F 9-5 office jobs.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "If you work in a warehouse, a production line or as a cashier, you cannot take calls and it can cause issues with a supervisor.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "As someone who has answered a company phone, you can tell a caller that the employee cannot take calls or that they don't work there, but that caller will repeatedly call back.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "My position on this is simple, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "if the creditor does not call to confirm employment before credit is issued, they should not call after the debt is in collection.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "policy", "text": "If they confirm employment then they could also inquire about the communication policy.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "testimony", "text": "Personally, I am in a position of constant public contact with no available phone with me and it would be hard to immpossible to have a phone conversation without leaving my work area which would cause issues with management for my job.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "759", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "There is now a class of \"consumer representatives\" which obtains from debtors a signed \"Power of Attorney\" and who then claim to be authorized to act as the consumer's attorney for purposes of debt resolution.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "They routinely seek to avoid the debt, most commonly by not answering their phones.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "My current practice is to advise the relevant state bar of the unauthorized practice of law by these jokers;", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "perhaps a clarification statement that such persons must be licensed to practice law in the state in which the debt is being collected would cut down on the confusion.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "501", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Consumers should be able to review all encoding and information in e-OSCAR", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "and there should be a comprehensive means to submit corrections and evidence to a dispute.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "512", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "To start e-oscar should take internet complaints the same a shad written letters.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "They do not do that.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "They take internet disputes differently then they do hand written letter.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "That is in regards to disputed debts and it is important that the credit bureaus be consistent about the dispute process and the statues of limitations based on state laws.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "They should also have limits on how many collection agencies they sell the account of too including their shady practice of selling accounts of to collection agencies in different states.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "Their should be a cap on debts owed and the power that the agencies have on consumers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "I think ultimatel it is about the collection agencies not abusing the consumer and helping consumers find ways to keep their accounts out default.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "A good start to offer consumers to get their accounts out of default would be based on charging consumers a small percentage of % coupled with a promissory note with a date to begin making payments to the debt collector.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "They abuse the consumers ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "policy", "text": "and they should stop it.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "Overall, the communication process between consumers and debt collectors is flawed with mis communications and a lack of options to pay back what they owe.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "199", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "To avoid consumers getting sued repeatedly on the same debt, the CFPB should require or encourage states to adopt rules requiring that judgments be preclusive of future consumer-collector litigation on the same debt;", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "instead, if there is a dispute between assignees as to who has title to the debt, they should work it out between themselves instead of risking subjecting the consumer to multiple liability.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "867", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I think that privacy concerns regarding account information are valid.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "Others knowing about collections should not weigh nearly as much as good-faith efforts of collectors to notify and collect outstanding debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "969", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "Our office throws a wide net around \"disputes\".", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "This is largely a hard one to define ", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "because it can take very specific and individual forms.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "Generally, however, the type of disputes we see center around when a debt buyer has purchased the debt and the consumer does not recognize the name of the debt buyer,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "they may generally state they don't owe the debt (with no further reasoning as to why not) or they don't owe as much as is being sought.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "Additionally, there may be claims of fraud or payment.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "Our office conservatively accepts verbal disputes as well as written.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "I think the greater issue is not what is considered a dispute,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "but how does a collector validate the debt?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "Many consumers ask for incredibly specific items.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "fact", "text": "There is a poor form letter that floats around the internet that many consumers find and use, in which the consumer requests verification not validation, whatever the difference in that may be, then demands specific information be provided.", "reasons": ["11_12"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "I say this because then I believe many consumers feel each of those requested items must then be provided,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "fact", "text": "when in fact the FDCPA is silent to the issue as to what proper verification is.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "value", "text": "I will leave that for another post, though my thought there will be defining what is verification will prove to be a difficult task ", "reasons": ["14"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "value", "text": "as you can't be so defined that the various types of creditors cannot possibly provide the information sought or so loosely defined that there is load of litigation needed to define it.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "314", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "If the consumer claims identity theft then the Debt collectors should be required to prove otherwise.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "The CRAs should be forbidden to report any debt that has been disputed as Identity theft unless they can provide court admissible proof that it is a valid debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "The CRAs should be held more accountable and heavily fined for reporting erroneous information.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "Their fines should be paid directly to the consumer for the countless hours they spend trying to fix their credit reports.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "The CRAs should be required to send a letter to the consumer's insurance companies, mortgage companies, and anyone else that charged the consumer a higher rate based on their erroneous credit score and find out how much their error costs the consumer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "The sum of those added costs should be paid by the CRAs directly to the consumer in addition to the fines.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "The burden of proof should fall on the CRAs and the debt collectors, not the consumer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "730", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "FDCPA 805(a)(1) is routinely violated by at least two large banks--Citicards and Wells Fargo.", "reasons": null, "evidence": ["1", "2_3"]}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "Both have called before 9 AM and after 8 PM.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "I live in the Central Time Zone", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "and no matter where these banks are based, they ignore that and call early and late.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "The mailing address should take priority", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "and it should not matter whether the collector is based in Portland, Oregon or Ft. Lauderdale, Florida,", "reasons": ["6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "if it's 8 AM in Chicago, they should not be calling.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1021", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I think the requirement for a debt collector to send a validation notice 5 days after the initial contact is backwards.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "I believe communication between the debtor and debt collector would be improved if the debtor has the validation notice before the initial telephone contact.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "The debt collector should be required to mail the debtor a validation notice 5 days before any phone contact, not 5 days after.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Otherwise, the debtor is speaking with an unknown caller, who has surprised them with a demand for money.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "The debtor has not been provided with any time to prepare their thoughts, or to formulate important questions about the alleged debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "They may be caught \"off guard\", increasing the fear and anxiety of the debtor, which would necessarily lead to impaired verbal communication.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "fact", "text": "The debtor has no written factual statement to refer to during the phone call, while the debt collector has all of the factual details in from of them on their computer screen, and can cite facts and figures.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "This situation creates an imbalance of power not conducive to good communication.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "This proposal to require debt collectors to send a validation notice 5 days before the first telephone contact would impose no financial burden on the debt collector, ", "reasons": ["9"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "fact", "text": "because validation notices are already required to be sent to the debtor.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "It is simply a change in the timing of an already existing requirement.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "372", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I disagree with the above assessment.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "As an alleged defaulter I have asked over and over and over again to have the debt set where it was at the time of alleged default and that no more penalties fees or interest rate charges be tacked on, and that I will commit to a monthly autopay.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "People who INVOLUNTARILY defaulted because of a life changing event in their lives (such as becoming caregivers for their parents) may want to consider all of their defaults together,", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "so if five defaults occurred, the alleged defaulter has to divide whatever money they may be able to apportion every month, by five.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "Debt collectors refuse to see this as a reasonable solution", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "and only acknowledge their own debt with the alleged defaulter, making it impossible for the alleged defaulter to do the right thing and begin paying back everybody.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1290", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "There are laws on the books.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "There is no enforcement by the regulators.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1247", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Email: Yes so long as it is not a \"blind\" email attempt at reaching an individual ", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "as it may reach the incorrect party (first.lastname@company.com when it should be first.lastname1@company.com", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "The down side to this is the inevitable fishing attacks by scammers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "Email should therefore be limited to times when the consumer initiates it or formally lists their email with the 3 major reporting agencies as a method of initial contact.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "409", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "while this isn't the best forum for me to go into my company's entire collection process, we work a debt for at least 120 days with letters, live agent calls, robo calls, emails, mailed invoices, and by suspending subscription service (where allowed) as part of our collection campaign.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "Even then, we only go to litigation after the debtor has been unresponsive to our attempts to contact them.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "I've found that if a debtor talks to their creditors, many times creditors will take their situation into account.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "I've offered lengthy repayment plans, reduced or waived interest or late fees, or partial settlement for those explain their hardship.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "But if a debtor is uncooperative or doesn't respond to our attempts to work out a balance, what other alternatives do creditors have?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1322", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "The original comment was suggesting that anytime a debt collector calls they are automatically agreeing to be recorded if the consumer chooses to do so.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "I think that is a FANTASTIC idea.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1361", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "They should not have free-to-end-user ", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "it will just making worse for consumer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "This does not make sense.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1345", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Student Loans, Many of the problems that students are facing are with student loans from the private sector.", "reasons": ["1_3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "Take for example Sallie Mae, this company has it on file that i dod not graduate from college ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "and i did graduate.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Their collections agencies are like loan sharks going to the extreme of making threats and cussing out students who cannot make payments.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "I know for some people it is easy to make payments on student loans ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "but for many it is a struggle to get by.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "All students are trying to better themselves ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "fact", "text": "and sometimes they simply cannot afford to make payments.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "Companies like Sallie Mae are in the business of making peoples lives miserable.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "fact", "text": "Their collection practices, customer service and lack of options are usually the reason why students default on their loans.", "reasons": ["10_11"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "Paying for college is a marathon not a sprint ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "and these companies treat the repayment of student loans like a sprint.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "policy", "text": "I think they need to offer more options to students.", "reasons": ["9"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "policy", "text": "I also think private institutions ala the schools that lend money to students need to do a better job at giving students options to prevent default. resolutions and remedy not judgement and default.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "574", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I like the Summary of Rights idea.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "I think that a validation letter and even an initial communication letter should included of Summary of Rights for State Laws and Fed Laws.", "reasons": ["2", "3", "4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "This would help two fold: both the debtors/consumers and the debt collecting companies.", "reasons": ["3", "4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "The debtor/consumers would know their rights ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "and the collectors would then also know the particular rights for the states that they are collecting in.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "This shouldn't be burdensome at all ", "reasons": ["6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "since the CRA already include Summary of Rights as do employers who check credit.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1356", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "During the past 2 years I have been repeatedly contacted by a variety of collection agencies.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "It began innocently enough, when one of them called me, asking \"when can we expect your payment,\" when that statement had not yet arrived and was not due until the 20th of the month and the call occurred on the 11th.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "It was a collection agency hired by Capital One.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "Coincidentally, I purchased various items at Costco a few days later and received the shock of my little life when my credit card was denied.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "I called Capital One from a phone at Costco and was told I had not made my payment...", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "this was even stranger", "reasons": ["6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "because I pay off my balance each month.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "What I didn't know is that Costco switched from a very nice bank (HSBC) to Capital One, never notified me ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "and Capital One immediately played hardball, albeit unnecessarily.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "testimony", "text": "To answer their strong-arm tactics, I wrote a letter to Robert Crawford, the incoming CFO of Capital One, in which I had cut up both credit cards and told him to \"shove it,\" for treating a long-time customer like something you scrape off the shoe!", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "When the collection calls began, I was in a great mood", "reasons": ["11"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "testimony", "text": "after all, I had initiated this mess.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "value", "text": "However, they were unfaird from the beginning.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "testimony", "text": "They use I.V.R. numbers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "fact", "text": "Without technical jargon, it means that the number we see on caller i.d. is never the number from which they're calling, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 15, "type": "fact", "text": "so you can't block their call", "reasons": ["14"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 16, "type": "testimony", "text": "my provider allows me to block 12 numbers ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 17, "type": "value", "text": "and I wondered how these collection agencies were constantly squeaking by).", "reasons": ["16"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 18, "type": "fact", "text": "They robodial, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 19, "type": "fact", "text": "so you can and do get several calls per day and before 8:00 AM and after 9:00 PM,", "reasons": ["18", "20"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 20, "type": "value", "text": "since they know there is very little you can do about the early or late calls, besides whine", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 21, "type": "value", "text": "That said, what followed was even worse....", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 22, "type": "testimony", "text": "the collection agency (Portfolio Recovery) which was able to place a bogus $9,924 \"collection\" on my Experian credit score, which I saw because Target offered me 1-year free credit monitoring, which, by the way, isn't free if you want to see your complete profile...", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 23, "type": "testimony", "text": "they have no paperwork to substantiate this charge ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 24, "type": "testimony", "text": "and it has completely ruined my credit, pulling down my FICO from 795 - 810 to 610!", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 25, "type": "value", "text": "To me, having collection agency CEO's boiled in oil seems like an act of mercy!", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "861", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I do not think that answering 97% of the calls from an automated dialer within two seconds is a solution to my problem.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "I would like for Mr. Dan to explain exactly what the safeguards of using a robo dialer are.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "From my perspective as a frequent recipient of robo calls from debt collectors, the problem is a lack of ownership and impersonality of the collection agency when the debt is not assigned to one collector to handle.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "Years ago when a collector would call me, it would always be the same person.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "Now it is not.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "Assign the debt to one collector who would then take full responsibility for making all contacts with the alleged debtor.", "reasons": ["3_4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "This could even include acquisition of location information.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1405", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I disagree.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Keeping a paper trail protects everyone, especially the most vulnerable and least able to protect oneself.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1131", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I meant to say, \"all lawyers should be banned from being debt collectors.\"", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "They are unethical and work strictly out of greed to circumvent the laws that are supposed to protect consumers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "Verification of debts should require the creditor to provide written proof of the initial debt instrument with the consumers' signature.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "There should be a notarized statement of authenticity along with it.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "This gives a consumer the documents to file a civil suit for fraud, if needed.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1050", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Though I do not agree with \"someone to rack up tens of thousands of dollars of debt and never pay it back\".", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "My current standing is that the laws of each and every state allow for higher interest rates to be charged for non-secured debt.", "reasons": ["2_3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "This is because the lenders take more losses ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "\"the risk should be in alignment with the award\".", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "In many cases the principal has been paid back in full or the majority of the debt has been paid back.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "To allow a \"third party\" to buy it at a significantly reduced price, after the debt has been charged off by the original \"lender/creditor\" AND allow the third party to collect the full alleged balance and interest is not just.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "This is the way I am leaning at this time.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "Explain to me why you or I feel differently?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "417", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "The most common consumer contact my firm receives as a dispute is the comment by the consumer on a call with the agency that \"it's not my debt\".", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "While that may be a true statement in some cases, some proof from the consumer should be required as to why the debt isn't theirs.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "For our customers, proof of residence at a different address from where our service was provided is usually sufficient for us to remove that customer from the debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "The consumers must understand that they have to work with the creditor or agency to correct whatever info lead to an \"incorrect link\" (common name, bad SSN, fraud...).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "The 3 items listed in CFPB summary is usually adequate.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "457", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "Consumers are typically notified numerous times before the account is sent to a collection agency.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "It is in the best interests of the credit union to try and resolve the delinquency before it is sent to a collection agency due to the added cost.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1197", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "When calling about a debt, debt collectors MUST verify that they are speaking to the debtor(s) or other adult within the household.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "I know that is stated within the FDCPA", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "but from experience I know it doesn't always happen.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "My situation goes back to the 1970's", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "but it was done then ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "and it's probably still being done today.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "Calling repeatedly, threatening, screaming, cursing at children gets collectors absolutely nowhere.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "It is a most disgusting form of abuse that should never be tolerated.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "policy", "text": "New language in the FDCPA should specifically and clearly state this.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "policy", "text": "Additionally, there should be some form of penalty for collectors who engage in this demeaning and useless practice.", "reasons": ["7"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1044", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "If consumers can receive phone calls on Sundays, there's no reason for them to not accept emails.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "Controlling which messages you get and how they are routed and presented to you, including what alerts or sounds they make when received, is only possible with email.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Email is far superior to any other communication medium.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1273", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "If a bank is going to sell a consumer's debt, the bank should be required to notify that consumer IN ADVANCE, and allow that consumer a fair chance to bid on and purchase his/her own debt, on terms just as favorable as the terms offered to any other debt buyer (which at present is usually pennies on the dollar).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Debt buyers contribute nothing to society.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Yet, they are allowed to obtain windfall profits by pursuing impoverished consumers for the full face value of such debts.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "This proposal would entail changes more extensive that just \"notice\" ", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "as it would require a change from bulk loan sales, to requiring an opportunity to purchase individual loan in certain circumstances.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "990", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have seen the \"moderator\" in the caller ID forum ask if it would be okay to put the company's name on the caller ID because this could show to others around that the person has a debt and would then compromise the consumer's privacy and security.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Yet, there is a discussion to allow these calls at a consumer's work?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "many people do not work in an office,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "so a message would have to be left with a secretary.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "This is letting someone else know of a debt who should not be privy to that information.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "The ONLY reason these companies have to calling someone at work is to publicly shame the person into paying.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "It is the modern version of putting someone in stockades and throwing fruit at them, or a modern scarlet letter.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "policy", "text": "If there is another phone number on an application, that is the one that needs to be used.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "policy", "text": "If there is an address on the application, that is what needs to be used.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "Calls to someone's work are off limits PERIOD!", "reasons": ["10"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "There is not way for the collection agency or the government regulation body to GUARANTEE that no one besides the consumer gets the information when someone's work is called.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1249", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "Social Media: While the courts have made the rare exception for use of social media as a means of giving notice, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": ["2"]}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "not everyone is on every social media platform.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "I am very internet savy yet I am not on foursquare, pinterest and several others.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "On FB, Twitter and others there are several thousand people with my name who may get incorrectly notified.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "824", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "Additionally the landlords real estate attorney also had a collections agency", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "so he continuously flipped the landlords debts into his agency", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "and again the landlords get to keep writing it off with each and every lawsuit,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "in this instance it was 8 lawsuits for the same amount.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "805", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "They have done so.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I've gotten calls from the same collector who will use a toll free, then a number with an area code, then that number will be changed by a digit.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "Google the number.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "That is so helpful.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "It will tell you the company that is calling.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "It was always the same on.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "I agree this is wrong, misleading, a fraudulent way to deal with people.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "But the totality of all I am reading here is that collectors are harassing and do it by phone.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "The thing to do is put some teeth into the laws that prevent this.", "reasons": ["11", "9_10"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "fact", "text": "Now, the only thing consumers can do is sue.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "And for $1000 -- and you'd be hard pressed to find a lawyer who will sue for such a small amount.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "It has become a situation that slams the consumer,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "value", "text": "it has evolved into that.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1024", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "The reason they can sell it for a fraction of what is owed is because the debt buyer is purchasing entire portfolios of bad debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "It spreads out the risk.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "If you can get a million other delinquent consumers to go in with you on a 10% offer, you could probably get them to take it.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "But it doesn't make financial sense for them to offer the same transaction to you as the debt buyer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1182", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "It is the responsibility of the creditor and debt collectors to report accurate information.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Reporting accurate information has nothing to do with \"debt collectors who don't report to credit reporting agencies at all.\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "If a debt collector reported accurately that the debt in question has not been paid, but now is, it is the responsibility of that debt collector to report the newly accurate information.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "As I too have noticed, some debt collectors will not accurately report updated information to the credit bureaus once they are paid.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "860", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "A contractor who did work unlicensed was able to file bogus claims against both me and my wife amounting to double the original bid price.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "there was no court action.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "I managed to get rid of the debt collector ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "but there seems nothing I could do to stop another contractor doing the same thing.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "There should be a penalty for the people filing the false debt.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "The amount in question was almost $10,000", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "681", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "All? It's just not so.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "Maybe retailers do;", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have no experience with them.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "But medical billers are consistently mistaken, careless, and just plain wrong.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "One medical facility called my daughter-in-law's cell phone about a bill for my mother!", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "They had her number as, I think, the fourth emergency number.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "And this was a GOOD place, that actually tried and finally managed to get in touch with me.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "I was very pleased with their billing department, compared to others we had dealt with.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "683", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Yep, that's right.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Isn't the point supposed to be to collect the debt?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1353", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "Having been recently included for free credit checking, after the Target identity theft issue, I checked my credit with Experian and found a $9,924 \"collection\" on my credit report, resulting in a 610 FICO score!", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I had never heard of Portfolio Recovery, a company located in Virginia.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "I immediately wrote to the Office of Consumer Affairs in Virginia, detailing what this erroneous addition to my credit report had done to my overall score and my ability to maintain good credit.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "ALL of my credit cards lowered my limits,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "but I thought that had been in response to the ongoing bank investigations and the banks way of getting back at consumers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "It all made sense when I saw this entry.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "What shocked, alarmed and enraged me most is that Experian excepted this \"collection\" entry without documentation.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "I can assure you that none exists.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "testimony", "text": "However, I have been a victim of lost wallets and identity theft within the last 20 years and may have seemed a legitimate target to Bottom-feeder agencies like Portfolio Recovery ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "(the Internet is rife with consumer complaints about their tactics and illegal practices attempting to collect \"debts!\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "I intend to pursue this matter by informing our Attorney General Kamala Harris and am grateful that you are targeting an otherwise unassailable lobby.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "Anytime a consumer writes to a credit reporting agency, the letter winds up in Mumbai, is laughed at and never acted upon.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "policy", "text": "Experian, TransUnion and Equifax should undergo a Congressional investigation, during which their anti-consumer orientation and fraudulent reporting will be noted, as well as the impossibility of restoring a former 810 FICO, once scumbags like Portfolio Recovery have been allowed clear access to ruin the credit score and compromise the professional life and earning potential of millions of consumers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "710", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I had a 19 year old debt come back to haunt me", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I went to three attorney's to attempt to pay them to \"talk\" to the company, as the information I was given, would not call me back after leaving several messages, along with an offer to settle it for slightly more than one-half of what they claimed I owed.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "This debt went from around $1200 up to $9,300 in those 19 years.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "This type of behavior must be regulated", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "it is only out and out a scam.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "623", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "This is a collectors favorite.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "They call over and over to harass debtors ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "and they should be limited to one call per day with a required voicemail stating their purpose.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1401", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Good idea debt neutrality.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "But the sad thing is, being in debt is NOT considered a crime", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "however, the way the laws are now, and the abuses these collection agencies engage in, you might as well be considered a criminal.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "I agree.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "Set up a system where the consumer is on equal footing with the debt collectors.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "388", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Very confusing if I can pay my student loans directly to DOE or to one of the many private companies who have owned my loan over the years.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "They continue to try to entice me to restructure the student loan debt - very misleading - without disclosure of their fees", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "at this point I cannot even trace a $30000 fee that was double billed to my total.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "It is a web of confusion that I cannot escape.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "I intend to take my student loans to my death", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "as I have no other way of making the monthly payments.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1094", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I have a hard time believing that a debt collection company \"treat[s] EVERY dispute the same\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "when debt collectors seem to blatantly disregard a dispute that has the appearance of being \"copied directly from the internet.\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Consumer advocates are trying to educate consumers, debtors, and alleged debtors with information on how to handle debt collectors or how to handle their particular situation.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "We are try to give them relevant links to FDCPA, FCRA, HIPPA, and various form letters that can help them communicate with debt collectors.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "There is nothing wrong with form letters.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "But there is everything wrong with debt collectors disregaring certain letters just because they don't like that it came from a consumer advocate source.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "Debt collectors operating legally and with nothing to hide should never treat form letters as something to throw in the trash.", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "You seem to be saying that debt collectors will only want to communicate with consumers who are misinformed and don't know what their rights are, rather than communicate with a consumer who knows the laws and the appropriate ways to address a letter of dispute.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1119", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "In the case of medical debt, the statement should inform the consumer of the date and location of the service provided, including the name of the doctor who was in charge of the case (rather than a consultant or firm that never contacted the consumer) or the commonly used name of the location (such as a hospital or clinic) where the service was performed.", "reasons": ["1_2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "In my experience, cost-conscious consumers who are wary of scams have declined to pay legitimate medical debt ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "because they did not recognize the debt and could not get an answer to the basic question, \"Why do I owe this money?\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "When the debt is unexplained, it is prudent to refuse to send money,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "yet when the debt is in fact legitimate, the consumer may suffer severe penalties for failure to pay.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "A validation notice for medical debt should not simply repeat numerical codes or obscure abbreviations.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "It should state, \"You were billed on (DATE) when you went to (PLACE).\"", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "policy", "text": "If other debts related to the same visit have been paid, the letter should say so, e.g., \"You already paid for other services during this visit, but you still owe...\" Or, \"Your insurance paid for some of the costs of this visit, but you still owe....\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "This issue is related to the absurd complexities of medical billing,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "policy", "text": "but those complexities should not be used to conceal the origin of a debt from a consumer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1167", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "This particular bill collector has in the past said that I owe $20.00 more as I had a non sufficient funds. [which I would not do].", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I disputed it with my bank statements ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "and still they insisted that I have.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "I refused to pay that.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "325", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I don't think the consumer should have the options as to when and how they are called.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Most collection agency's today would remove a consumers phone number hen asked.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "218", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "No federal rules.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "Allow States continued enforcement of their state laws.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "451", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Compliance 2013 demonstrates the type of arrogance that I have been addressing in my prior comments.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "The belief that a default is a default by courts along with the practice of REWARDING Strategic Defaulters while sentencing INVOLUNTARY DEFAULTERS to never ending escalating debt because of the ongoing interest rate charges needs to be addressed.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have been researching consumer debt for the past few years ", "reasons": null, "evidence": ["5"]}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "and Consumer Debt is ON THE RISE GLOBALLY,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "and that is not a good thing.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "reference", "text": "<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.winnipegfreepress.com/business/too-much-debt-in-the-developed-world-chilton-230947131.html\">Canadian finance expert warns about rising consumer debt.</a>", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "fact", "text": "I can replace Canada in the title with England, Australia, South Africa, China, Russia, Ireland and on and on and on.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "fact", "text": "The consumer debt escalation is being caused by a ridiculously low 2% monthly minimum payment, the gateway drug to higher and higher debt, and because consumers who have legitimate life Changing events that cause them to default cannot plead INVOLUNTARY DEFAULT in court.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "fact", "text": "We let criminals plead involuntary to many crimes, but not law abiding citizens when it comes to their credit cards and student loans!", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "579", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "I think there should be a fed law that should clearly state that any partial payment might revive the SOL for suit.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "How consumers get a phone call/letter telling them they have a debt and they just blindly pay it or make partial payments in order to just stop getting the phone calls? Lots.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "And the debt might not even be theirs, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "but they pay it anyways thinking that they might have a old debt that they forgot to take care of.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "The problem with that is, that the debt then is revived, the debt collector sues, and the judge tells the debtor \"well, if this wasn't your debt then why did you agree to make partial payments?\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "Then the judge will make favor in the debt collector for a revived debt that the debtor was not even responsible for in the first place.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "fact", "text": "This scenario happens every day of the week.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "And the consumer had thought they were doing the right thing, but the debt collector is actually taking advantage.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1040", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "I believe lawsuits should be initiated in the jurisdiction in which the consumer resides,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "and that the case should be subject to the laws of that jurisdiction, especially concerning the statute of limitations.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Yes, I realize that a SOL defense is an affirmative one).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1301", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Consumers normally are unaware that their debt has been sold to a collection agency.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "They, one day, get a call about the debt from someone unbeknownst to them.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "The collection agency wants the consumer to remit the payment to them, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "when actually, principal on the debt never decreases ", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "because the collection agency gets their cut (commission) off the top.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "The debt is there essentially, forever with added late charges, interest and other penalties.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "I submit to the CFPB to finalize the \"Know Before You Owe\" rule and to outlay the debt validation rules", "reasons": ["7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "so that consumers can make an informed choice before wasting their money on a debt they may not owe.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1137", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "The Consumer Finance Protection Bureau needs to have a large core of undercover agents that get jobs at collection agencies, credit agencies and servicers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "These agents need full federal law enforcement powers with guns and badges", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "so they can perp-walk suspects out of their offices and take them to federal holding facilities for trial when they have proof of criminal activity.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Currently it seems many creditors, servicers and debt collectors consider themselves above the law.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "There's only two ways to discourage that thinking and that's jail time and/or fines.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "After conviction, victims should receive a framed and signed (first name or nickname of the agent) photograph of the perp-walk.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "fact", "text": "They usually don't get their money back", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "but that's something they will treasure.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1241", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "In NYC courts, a lawyer representing a particular party (doesn't have to be collection related) will have a full day of cases lined up", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "which leads me to believe at least some scheduling preference is given.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "592", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "A neighbor who has since moved away has had her debts turned over to collection agencies.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "We receive repeated calls trying to get contact information, even though we request to be taken off their list.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "An unfortunate situation but we don't know the whereabouts of the individual and shouldn't be subjected to this sort of harassment.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "679", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "My daughter has both private and federal loans through Sallie Mae.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "They call her cell phone and my cell phone daily, at least 10 times a day.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "They called me,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "by the way, they do not have her permission to speak with me, and tell me to stop paying her federal loans because they can be deferred and pay the private loans.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "My daughter owes 176000.00 in private loans and can't afford to make the payments that they are asking for.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "They called her employer requesting information on her.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "She sent a letter and requested that they only contact her through email and US mail.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "When they called me I asked them if they received this", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "testimony", "text": "and they said yes but they need to be able to talk to someone.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "testimony", "text": "Well, they don't have my number as a contact number.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "testimony", "text": "I told them and they still call my cell phone daily.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "testimony", "text": "My daughter can barely pay the bills she has now.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "testimony", "text": "I help her pay her private loans.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "testimony", "text": "I am not on any of her loans.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "policy", "text": "This harassment needs to stop!", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "644", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "The national database and licensing would be a good idea if it were used effectively to weed out the bad collectors and put them (and their corporate officers) out of business permanently. Not those who get caught up in technical violations over mini-Mirandas, but the ones who knowingly commit serious violations of the FDCPA, FCRA, and TCPA.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "As Tfleeman noted in his very insightful comment above, the \"private policing\" we have now has not been effective in stopping the worst abuses.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "As for the main topic of this page, I think it's far better for a collector to leave a voicemail (with clear identification of the caller and callee) than to call the same number 50 times without leaving a message.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "The rules should encourage this rather than frustrate it.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "So, I would favor option #1, with the mini-Miranda deferred until the collector is sure he is talking to the right person.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1026", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I agree that it benefits everyone when notice of sale or assignment is given to the consumer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "I am not aware of any part of the industry other than mortgage servicers who presently give notice.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "The benefit is clear", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "it reduces confusion, reduces the risk of misapplied/lost payments, and produces a clear chain of ownership.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "It would be costly to the creditors selling the debt, but not so much as to be prohibitive.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "Creditors have to send notices under a variety of other laws.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "I don't think this addition would make that much of a difference.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "policy", "text": "I think the notice should state the account number, the entity to who it is being sold (including contact information) and the amount currently owed.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "policy", "text": "It should be sent by the seller, who has the most current information for the consumer, and a copy should be provided to the debt buyer as part of the sale package.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1027", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "From a collection standpoint, I can tell you that many creditors would LOVE to check with the DMV to get current address information.", "reasons": ["1", "2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "Unfortunately, many privacy laws make that impossible.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "It's also extremely common for people to fail to update their addresses either with their creditors or with the post office.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Any legitimate collector wants to find the right person.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "464", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "The entire point of collectors calling debtors at work is to intimidate and cause fear of loss of employment to the debtor ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "and the practice should be outlawed unless the debtor opts in to receive calls there.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "Its well known that companies like Sallie Mae will continue to call debtors at work even after being told not to.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "498", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have a debt in dispute with the CFPB, and it has not yet been resolved, but during the government shutdown the Original Creditor turned it over to a collection agency.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "The collection agency has not contacted me in writing at all, but they did a hard pull on my credit report.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "I legitimately closed the account when it was paid in full, but they continued billing me after I had cancelled the service.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Now the matter is simply snowballing.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "I am very upset about this.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "If a consumer is in the midst of a dispute with the CFPB, I would think there would be a \"time out\" on collection actions and especially malicious hard pull of the credit report while the dispute is ongoing.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1418", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "reference", "text": "For further reference on debt tolling: http://collectionagencydebt.blogspot.com/2012/08/tolling-debt-and-statute-of-limitations.html", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "So, again, it seems as though the SOL matters very little in these cases.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Perhaps the bigger question is whether or not eliminating debt tolling should be considered as a new rule.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "953", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I used to have a lot of debt and told every single company that called to send me something in the mail.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I paid every single debt that I received mail for.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "Years later someone went after me ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "and me, not knowing the rules, got stuck with it.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "I still have not seen anything in writing to even verify what the debt is for ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "- and the court wasn't any better - ", "reasons": ["6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "I didn't even have a chance to talk to the judge.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "How is this right?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "570", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I guess I don't exactly understand the response.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "I suppose getting the credit report on paper is useful,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "but online one can actually fix multiple errors and then be notified once the changes have been made.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "575", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "There should never be a fee for payment.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "In fact, in about 1/3 of the states have state laws that prohibit any fees/surcharges for payment by credit/debit cards (unless it is a government agency).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "if a debt collector accepts credit/debit cards for payment, there should not be any fees for payment processing.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "Nor should there be any fees for payment processing for any other payment method for that matter.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "debt collection companies should also be able to accept prepaid debit cards for payment as a means of privacy and security for the debtors, rather than access to a bank account.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1192", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "It could be treated just like any document you fax or snail mail,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "uploading is just an easier way to get it there.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "As to fine time, I would say 48 hours.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1227", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I live in Florida where proof of the debt is getting difficult for debt buyers to prove without them falsifying documents.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I currently have a case where the Debt bill of sale was whited out in three places,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "sadly these documents were filed by an attorney at law registered with the Florida Bar Association.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Debt buyers have no scruples", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "692", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Alternative one is the easiest to communicate and probably the easiest to understand.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Accouting systems will vary from creditor to creditor", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "and requirements beyond this would only become more cumbersome and costly for a creditor and more confusing for a consumer.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "I would not have the breakdown be different for different types of credit extended.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "Computers and brains all across America will start smoking.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1219", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I agree that expanding the scope of the validation notice would benefit consumers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Especially important is a means for the consumer to contact the original creditor and identify the account in question.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "When debts are sold multiple times it becomes impossible for consumers to: (1) determine if the account is theirs; (2) validate proper assignment; and (3) determine if the statute of limitations has expired.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "The current requirements facilitate \"zombie debt\" accounts which - although already paid by the consumer - come back to life again and again.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "Absent a means for consumers to identify an account there is no way for them to verify that they have previously paid that debt.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "210", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I'm aware of that,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "but I don't think many appellate courts have considered the issue.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "To confirm that it's the law, it should be included in a rule.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1108", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "it should be a fdcpa violation to spoof a debt collector's phone number on the caller ID.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "Either no number on the caller ID or a number linked back to the collection agency.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1165", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "Technology does not allow debtors or alleged debtors to distinguish land lines from cellphones of debt collectors; whether private or federal.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "There appears to be a double standard between the debtor and collector.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have received calls after business hours and sometimes even on a Sunday from a mortgage servicer, whom I will not disclose.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "This particular servicer has even left an anonymous type of flyer (one that can be hung on a doorknob) with instructions to call the specific servicer's customer service phone number; without disclosing the name of the servicer, although I was already familiar with the phone number.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "I would classify this as mail fraud", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "because it bypassed the mail system.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "The same scenario with the service of process regarding my old school loan.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "fact", "text": "The service of process bypassed the mail system", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "policy", "text": "These are both issues that should be resolved collectively by and among the FCC, FTC and DOJ (not all inclusive).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "fact", "text": "A debt collector can call the debtor from a phone number outside of the collector's company", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "fact", "text": "so it won't be included in the company's phone log.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "fact", "text": "If the debtor attempts to return the phone call, the number is either inoperable or not able to receive incoming calls.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "fact", "text": "Collectors may even call a debtor in order to attempt them to give personal information about lowering the interest rate on their credit card (even if the debtor doesn't have a credit card).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "fact", "text": "It is obvious or apparent that there may be a credit card floating around in the debtor's name unknowingly.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "testimony", "text": "These are all scenarios I have experienced.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 15, "type": "value", "text": "We haven't gotten to the subject of sharing a debtor's information among the debtor's financial institution and the financial institution's correspondent institutions and investment advisor affiliates and other business combinations of the debtor (public utilities companies, mortgage servicers, insurance companies, pension fund mgrs, etc...", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1394", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "CG I endorse and want to add again at the risk of sounding like a broken record, it is the wild fluctuation in rules across the country.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "This is not a \"state's rights\" issue as someone wants to make it, but a way to bring some fairness and intelligence to this process.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1187", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have a charged off debt I want to pay off.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I cannot afford a lump sum and asked the debt collector and original lender in writing mutiple times to work with me on a settlement.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "They refuse to answer my letters", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "and I keep writing every month.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "I think they should be made to at least respond to a customer requests for repayment.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "They keep asking for my employer name and bank account number", "reasons": ["6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "because I know they want to use it to garnish my wages and bank account.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "Of course I do not have $32k to settle.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "testimony", "text": "It was a 2nd mtg,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "testimony", "text": "I lost home due to loss of job,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "testimony", "text": "they refused to modify", "reasons": ["11"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "testimony", "text": "because they said investor wanted to foreclose instead.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "480", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "Paying a debt in full will always improve a credit score unless the debt is over 7 years old.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "If that is the case, I'm sure you can make a request to the financial institution to not report the payment.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "612", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "A collector's toll-free number is the ideal number to display on Caller ID,", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "since it allows the call to be returned from anywhere without incurring long-distance charges.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "It also lets the recipient know right away that it is not a personal call and is probably not from a local company.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "I'd much rather see an 800 number than a spoofed local number for a company that is really 1000 miles away (or in India).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "This spoofing is clearly a false and deceptive practice that is barred by the FDCPA, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "but still it occasionally happens.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1146", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I was flat out lied to by the attorney for a credit card company who brought a small claims suit against me. ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I disputed the debt (and still do even after they garnished my wages", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "but they intimidated me into a payment arrangement then lied to me and said there was no court date anymore since I \"settled\".", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "I was skeptical and called the clerk of court's office only to find out they lied", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "and I did need to show up.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "I showed up for the court date, even as I argued that this court had no jurisdiction over me because I never lived in that county", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "but no-one even the clerk's office would listen to me", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "and I was denied the right to go before a judge.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "testimony", "text": "I was only given an opportunity to talk to the attorney for the credit card company and sign papers saying we had a payment arrangement.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "testimony", "text": "Long story short, I made 1 of 2 payments then lost my job.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "testimony", "text": "I called them immediately to tell them I would make the 2nd and final payment 2-3 weeks late because I had to wait for a final check.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "testimony", "text": "They told me okay,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "testimony", "text": "but unbeknownst to me,they went back to court without me and got a default judgement for $1600 on what would have been a $709 payment.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "testimony", "text": "iI never got notice of the court hearing ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "testimony", "text": "nor did I ever get a copy of the judgement.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 15, "type": "value", "text": "I didn't find out about it until I got a wage garnishment notice from my new employer 2 1/2 years later....VERY humiliating!", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 16, "type": "testimony", "text": "My employer got the wage garnishment notice a week before I did", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 17, "type": "testimony", "text": "so I couldn't even dispute it before my employer was involved.", "reasons": ["16"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 18, "type": "testimony", "text": "Second, I called the clerk of court's office in that county (3 hours from my home) and argued that you can't go to court without giving me a chance to defend myself and I shouldn't be forced to drive 3 hours each way to a county I never lived in.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 19, "type": "testimony", "text": "I was told by the clerk's office that they can file it wherever they want and I have to show up.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 20, "type": "testimony", "text": "I asked \"So if they wanted to file this in California to be jerks you're telling me I'd have to get on a plane and fly to California to defend a $709 lawsuit\"\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 21, "type": "testimony", "text": "She said \"Yes.\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 22, "type": "policy", "text": "THAT HAS TO CHANGE.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "984", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "My concern about a \"reasonable\" investigation is that it is so subjective.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "It opens the collector up to an entirely new avenue of prosecution.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "It is unlikely that a consumer and collector are ever going to agree on what is \"reasonable\".", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "As it stands now courts have steadfastly maintained that collectors are allowed to rely on information given to them by their clients: ie: a debt for an amount stated against consumer so and so.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "Beyond that the consumer and the collector have the ability to ask a third party, a judge, to make a determination.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "By all appearances the FTC and the CFPB would place this burden directly on the collector, with predictable results: more needless litigation over the process and less resolution regarding the debt itself.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "One alternative might be for the rule to state a set formula for verification along with the proviso that if the collector follows it they are provided a safe harbor from litigation.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "However the myriad possibilities for reasonable investigation probably preclude anything so simple.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "In the end I think it is still a judges purvey to make the final determination.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1331", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Yes. I think there is a way to get the debt collectors on board.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "The CFPB can remind them that debt collection companies may be exposing their own phone reps / employees to unnecessary verbal abuse from customers who have a legitimate justification for being upset because of follow up calls that ignore the updated agreement just reached in the prior call.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "If the previous communication with the debt collector creates a new timeline for possible repayment, then the debt collector should not step on that timeline by making subsequent calls less than a week later. unless the customers says call back in less than a weeks time.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "This also gives the debt collection phone rep the ability to say...\"It has been a week or longer since our last communication\"...Which allows the customer a moment to realize they are not being harassed on a daily basis by the same debt collector.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "Some consumers have situations in which their income grinds to zero ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "and they may default on more than one account.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "Imagine 5 debt collectors each calling twice a day.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "fact", "text": "Even one call a week can still equal one call a day if a consumer has five simultaneous defaults,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "but that is certainly preferable to 2 calls a day from each collection account, which would equal 10 calls a day, every day.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "410", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "The CFPB should require debt sellers to contact the debtor and inform them the debt has been sold.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "Additionally, ALL pertinent information must be given to the debtor to eliminate any confusion.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "Furthermore, the seller of the debt must be required and enforced to annotate the debtors credit report with the sale to help eliminate confusion and in a way to not increase the bad debt.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "Essentially, debts that are sold sometimes appear as two seperate debts on a consumers report which increases the penalty of having bad debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "A consumer should not be penalized twice for 1 debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1382", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "There are a few states that have the barbaric practice of actually arresting people for their debts by using a legal loophole.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Some of the most egregious examples are in Minnesota, Illinois, and Missouri.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "The creditor sues the debtor in court.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "If the person fails to show, a warrant can be issued for their arrest.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "The police can actually arrest and jail the debtor until a court hearing, or until they pay the bond (which is usually the amount of the debt).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "This is a downright abuse of the legal system.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "These loopholes need to be closed in all states.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1386", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "i agree. ", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "their comments are outrageous and is just more of the same.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "why should we expect a lobby group of debt collectors to really want enforceable new rules?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1288", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "The problem is enforcement.", "reasons": ["1_2", "2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "When collectors are notified to stop calling the consumer's workplace, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "they refuse to obey the law that requires them to stop.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Reporting violations to the regulators is futile, ", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "because nothing is ever done by way of enforcement and the collectors know this.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "Put teeth into enforcement.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "310", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "My company calls, auto-dials, emails, and snail mails customers many times before they are sent to a collection agency.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "Many debtors simply refuse to respond to the original debtor.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "They only make payment after the account is assigned to a collection agency -- akin to seeing just how far they can go before there's a consequence to not making payment.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "Requiring a validation notice from the owner of the debt should be optional on the creditor's part.", "reasons": ["4", "5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "The FDCPA requires the collection agency to send their first notice after the debt is assigned.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "More notices from the creditor are useless and expensive.", "reasons": ["7_9"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "fact", "text": "And the single most frequently used excuse of any debtor is \"I didn't receive the letter/invoice/statement\".", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "fact", "text": "A first class letter costs $0.55 minimum (inclusive of postage, paper, and envelope).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "fact", "text": "That cost does not include overhead and employee cost.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "Multiply that cost by the number of notices and statements already sent (and ignored) and you begin to see the true cost of collection.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "406", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "If a consumer is notified that their debt has been sold, there should be a way to contact the original creditor to verify.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "e. there should be a paper trail", "reasons": ["2", "4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "I see an opportunity for scam artists to claim that (as they are now) the consumer owes money to them and to pay off their debt immediately to the scam artist.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "With a clear paper/electronic trail, the path a debt takes from creditor to collector to collector can be verified and authenticated for the consumer's peace of mind,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "and so the right party gets paid.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1210", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I had an issue where an attorney,acting on my behalf,requested verification of the loan debt and never heard back from the collector.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "Therefore can not move ahead with settlement until they respond.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "206", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "The original creditor has information about the debtor's language;", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "ii) The collector obtains information about the debtor's language; *or*", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "iii) The debtor lives in a ZIP code known to have a significant (5%?) number of non-English speakers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "This requirement should only apply to languages with large LEP populations - a threshold might be 100,000 - to avoid undue cost.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "For smaller populations, where obtaining a full translation might be uneconomical, collectors could include the following passage translated into the appropriate languages on an otherwise English letter:", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "405", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Hardships are not all the same", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "and some hardships can last for a year or longer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "As a consumer advocate I see very few creditors that are willing to do anything more than refer to CCC or reduce rates for a short period of time.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "786", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Probably won't find any legislation", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "since people who have allegedly defaulted on a debt aren't necessarily going to tell the world, or create a lobby for their cause.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Debt Defaults and Debt Collections are a one sided issue in which judges have been constrained to simply determine if a default has occurred, or not.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "The lawyers primarily work with strategic defaulters", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "because S.D.'s have some source of money or income available to pay both the attorney and a partial portion of the debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "Involuntary Defaulters are left to fend for themselves", "reasons": ["6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "because they don't have money to pay a lawyer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "Debt Neutrality, in which an involuntary defaulter agrees they owe the debt and simply want's to be able to pay it down based on the amount the debt was at the time of the default, with no more penalties, interest rate charges, or fees, even if it takes 10 years to pay off the debt, would possibly alleviate a large amount of unnecessary court cases.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "And of course, once the very modest initial payments were set up, the account would no longer register as a negative on a debtor's credit score or credit rating.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "And to safeguard fraud, the debtor would not be able to keep borrowing larger and larger amounts of money until after their defaults were paid in full.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "It's a very logical solution in my opinion.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "Judges should be able to use logic to solve the growing backlog of credit card default cases.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "823", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "It's a good question,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "but unfortunately the answer is (of course) complicated.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Manually dialing phones slows down businesses and raises costs;", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "Automated dialing has preventive measures built in that manually dialing does not.", "reasons": ["9"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "To expand on the first point, debt collectors are cost centers, meaning their primary goal is to minimize costs (i.e., delinquent monies).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "An automated dialing system allows for a much more efficient manner of calling delinquent account-holders.", "reasons": ["7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "fact", "text": "Representatives are able to review the account history and status while the system connects the call,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "so the rep can quickly engage the customer.", "reasons": ["6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "If a customer has given their cell phone or home number to the lender knowing it may be used for future contact attempts, there is no difference to the customer if the call is executed through a computer or dialer on the keypad.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "To expand on the second point, automated dialing systems have a lot of built in controls that actually protect the consumer.", "reasons": ["11", "13"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "People make mistakes, and so do collectors:", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "fact", "text": "Automated dialers can have filters in place that restrict calls to customers based on location, time of day, or even how many attempts have already been made.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "fact", "text": "In addition, calls made through the dialer can all be recorded", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "value", "text": "so if there is a problem with the representative, the customer can refer back to the recording and the truth will come out.", "reasons": ["12"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "888", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Simplicity ought to be the guiding principle", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "and Alternative # 2 is closest to that principle,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "but expressions like \"charge-off\" should be avoided.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "That's a technical term specific to accountants.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "Some average consumers just aren't going to know what it means).", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "Beginning with the amount owed on the date of default, then adding interest (including rate) is simple enough,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "still, the calculation of that interest could be included).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "policy", "text": "Any and all fees ought to be listed, explained and JUSTIFIED.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "policy", "text": "The same should hold true for any other charges, followed by payments and/or credits added after the date of default.", "reasons": ["9"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "This presentation would provide a clear picture.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "964", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Enlisting the help of an attorney or other intermediary should also be considered a dispute.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I had both my attorney and my financial advisor contact my lender.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "Emails, phone calls and letters all constitute disputes.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "I think somehow it should be taken into account that a consumer may not know the specific cause of the dispute but they may know that the end result is wrong.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "I knew I had made \"x\" number of principal payments on my loan ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "and my lender claimed I had made \"y\" number of principal payments.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "I had emails and cancelled checks supporting the \"x\" number of payments ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "and the history from my issuing bank also supported my case and dates.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "testimony", "text": "My lender refused to investigate, saying they had done everything just as I asked and I had instructed them to apply \"y\" number of payments to principal.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "testimony", "text": "They had no documentation to back up this assertion ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "testimony", "text": "(their documentation was just a statement of how they processed my payments, not any of my direction).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "testimony", "text": "In order to get my situation fixed, I had to find the specific payment the lender misapplied from their own records, which were a mess due to the amount of errors they had made.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "value", "text": "This was not an easy task,", "reasons": ["13"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "value", "text": "as it was time consuming and the lenders records were not exactly layperson friendly reading.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "value", "text": "A couple of things... the average joe may not be able to read an institution's financial recordkeeping.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 15, "type": "value", "text": "In my case, my bank's history, cancelled checks and emails were all sufficient proof to my mind and the extent of consumer responsibility.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 16, "type": "value", "text": "At that point, the institution needed to justify their claim beyond \"we did what you told us to do\" and to provide proof of exactly that.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "658", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Wow, I didn't even know we had those rights", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "except for the one about the workplace, they're all news to me.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "So I've no experience,", "reasons": ["0", "1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "but my guess would be that the debt collectors would rather not receive this information.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1085", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Just to make my comment clear: I implied that the Free-to-end-user alternatives (if allowed to be used) need to be regulated ", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "so that they are not selling phone numbers and compromising the privacy of the consumers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "My comment made it appear as though I think that the free texting apps (which allow people to text for free) and the free-to-end-user alternatives are the same thing.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "They are not.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "I don't want the free-to-end-user alternatives to behave the same as free texting apps -- selling phone numbers to Spammers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1057", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Either State or Federal law should provide some penalty for passing an NSF or \"closed account\" check that includes a presumption of guilt.", "reasons": ["1", "2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "The check either bounced or it did not.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "There's not a lot of grey area here.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "That said, either State or Federal law should also allow the drafter of the check a \"safe harbor\" wherein they can pay the face value of the check and some nominal compensation for the hardship suffered by the recipient of that check in order to avoid this penalty.", "reasons": ["4_5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "Michigan has such a procedure ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "and it seems relatively equitable.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1147", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I support these restrictions on robo-calling and any calls during the work hours.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "With respect to robo-calls, any robo-calls that are misleading should be restricted.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "That is, a robo-call that tells you that you have a message or an account update, and the only way to get it is to call a special number with an extension, but when you call, it is just the same message asking where your payment is, is a waste of the consumer's time and the consumer's cellular resources (two phone calls, one received, one sent).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1136", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "A central system has privacy concerns", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "and it would be useful only if it included verification of who picked up the document and when.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "Instead creditors and debt buyers should be mandated to allow secure document uploading to their own website with official notification that the document has been reviewed.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have a pending case of a company misapplying my payments,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "I had to send many registered letters and faxes with proof of payment which cost some money and time.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "With this company anything you send them \"doesn't exist\" unless you have verifiable proof they have been forced to accept it.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "It would be a lot easier for the consumers to just upload the documentation and get verification the company reviewed it which can be used for a complaint.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "policy", "text": "There should be penalties of fines for not marking an uploaded document as \"reviewed\" after a period of time.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "660", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "The main problem with privacy is that we use the SS# for everything, so everything can be connected.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "That's been a bad idea since they started using it as a taxpayer i.d.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "It probably prevents a little fraud,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "but it's not worth it.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "We have, in effect, made it illegal to be untraceable--not a good thing for victims of domestic abuse, among others.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "500", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "You don't answer you'll get a call again.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "Rather than ignore you could answer and ask the company not to call you.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1409", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "it still bothers me that \"financial literacy\" may be the escape clause that the CFPB uses to avoid the real issue.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "How about rewarding those of us who have tirelessly blogged about exposing the financial traps set up by the credit card companies, especially those of us who did it all on our own dime and time.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "Credit Cards are THE BIGGEST PROFIT MAKING scheme in the U.S., much bigger than the mortgage industry.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "And as the CFPB knows, any type of money making machine gets protected through lobbying.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "That is exactly why the CFPB was able to fine the credit card companies well over 1/2 billion dollars for aggressively marketing the credit-protector Insurance program.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "When something makes so much money so easily, people just can't help themselves to try and keep expanding the money making venture.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "I personally warned about the credit card credit protector programs almost FIVE YEARS BEFORE the CFPB made their over half billion in fines.", "reasons": null, "evidence": ["7"]}, {"id": 7, "type": "reference", "text": "<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.credit-protector.com\">Credit-Protector</a>", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "testimony", "text": "I created my site on my own time and with no funding,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "policy", "text": "and I think my warning almost five years before should matter.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "I also don't understand why someone like myself who created my warning so early on, with no funding, can't be compensated on any level simply as a way to energize future generations that if they take the time and show they care for something that matters, they may someday be publicly rewarded/acknowledged.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "testimony", "text": "I also created blogs about Chase Bank and their credit card shenanigans back in 2009.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "fact", "text": "Once again, the class action lawyers swooped in and took 25 million dollars in legal fees.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "testimony", "text": "I didn't see a dime for my blogging", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "value", "text": "even though my 2009 protest blogs probably helped fuel the justified anger by some consumers who then went on a mission to get a class action lawyer involved.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 15, "type": "testimony", "text": "Once again, I got nothing.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 16, "type": "value", "text": "If Government Consumer Organizations are not willing to acknowledge those who care and show it, the system may never truly improve.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 17, "type": "reference", "text": "<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.daily-protest.blogspot.com\">Daily-Protest</a>", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 18, "type": "reference", "text": "<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bloggersagainstchasebank.blogspot.com\">Bloggers Against Chase Bank</a>", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 19, "type": "reference", "text": "<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.parallelforreclosure.blogspot.com\">Parallel Foreclosure</a>", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 20, "type": "reference", "text": "<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.swarmthebanks.blogspot.com\">Swarm The Banks</a>", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 21, "type": "reference", "text": "<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.wallstreetchange.blogspot.com\">Wall Street Change</a>", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 22, "type": "value", "text": "I have gone out of my way to offer financial literacy through the exposure of unfair credit card and banking policies for several years now.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 23, "type": "value", "text": "The tree fell, people heard it, but no one made a sound.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1164", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "As a college grad since 1979 and a first-time homebuyer, I have found widespread violations of the FDCPA among the creditors and their outsourced private collections agencies.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I've also found and been a victim of deception in the debt collection practice observing poor record keeping on the part of all parties.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "We must first examine debt collection from a derivative and forensic viewpoint; corporate finance, federally/state funded institutions and their debt obligations.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "GAAP allows for the write-off of old debts.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "Yet and still the creditors outsource collection agencies to collect debts the creditor has written off of their balance sheet.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "The debtor is always subject to the debt", "reasons": ["6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "fact", "text": "because the collection agency takes a percentage", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "fact", "text": "Then comes the finance charge (interest) and late payment charges.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "fact", "text": "In essence, the original debt remains the same", "reasons": ["9"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "fact", "text": "because the debtor is only paying commission, interest and late charges.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "testimony", "text": "I attended a Texas private college (state funded) that lost its accreditation for mismanagement of funds.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "testimony", "text": "My financial aid consisted of the BEOG, NDSL, Stafford Loan and the Merit Scholarship.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "fact", "text": "The school policy was to clear the balance of my bill before my grades were released.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "testimony", "text": "Each grade period, whatever the balance was, my Mom used the funds she had left from our Social Security Income (father deceased 1972) after paying monthly expenses to send to me for my grades to be released.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "fact", "text": "After my marriage, the Dept of Ed (Higher Ed) offset two years of joint tax returns, private collection agencies constantly called.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 15, "type": "testimony", "text": "When I was employed, I voluntarily paid $50/mo. for two years on this debt of which the principle was $4,650.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 16, "type": "testimony", "text": "Even after over 30 yrs., the debt was recorded as a Federal Abstract of Judgement at the county registrar (filed by private attorneys) as if I still owe the debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 17, "type": "value", "text": "I wasn't properly served.", "reasons": ["16"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 18, "type": "testimony", "text": "The process server (whomever it was) left a large manila envelope.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 19, "type": "testimony", "text": "Now the debt has been turned over to the Dept. of Justice in the State of Michigan.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 20, "type": "value", "text": "My point is that there is a widespread conflict of interest among the creditor and those outsourced by the creditor for debt collection.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 21, "type": "fact", "text": "Most, if not all of these organizations are operated by taxpayer funding.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 22, "type": "value", "text": "The taxpayers are the ultimate creditors.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1383", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I've heard multiple stories of summons being dropped off or served to the wrong individual and summons being mailed to old addresses when the new address was clearly available.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "I don't believe that a summons should ever be served by mail. ", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "If the debt collector wants to sue, they should be required to serve the person directly in the city and state in which they currently reside.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "It's an especially dirty tactic to serve someone by mail.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "It's unreliable and puts the debtor at a disadvantage.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1235", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Honest, respectful and open communication between consumers and collectors should be the goal.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "If there are too many roadblocks to making contact with a debtor, more consumers will find negative information on their credit reports and have more lawsuits filed against them.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Rule number 1 strikes the right balance.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "If the consumer responds, the consumer will receive the mini-miranda disclosure and information about the debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "If the named person is not at the number, is it really so awful to call the collector and let them know?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "If calls contiue after that point from the same collector, then there should be penalties.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "Professional collectors do not want to waste time calling a wrong number.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "806", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "This is a violation of the FCRA (Fair Credit Reporting Act) and can be corrected quickly by the credit reporting agency.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "If the credit reporting agency refuses, there are many Consumer Protection Attorneys that would happily take this case on contingency.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "This type of violation normally never sees the inside of a court room.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "A letter from a well known CP Attorney will likely get awards and the prompt correction of the credit report.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "476", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Consumers need to be pro-active in everything they do.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "If an individual had the capability to take on a debt then they should have the capability to resolve the debt.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "Every credit union I know goes the extra mile to help their members achieve financial success.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "856", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I assume by \"free to end\" you meant the agency is on the hook for the charges incurred on that particular call.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "I think it would be well worth exploring.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "We do have situations where the consumer doesnt have a landline and refuses access to their cell.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "If we recieve a cease and desist order we note the account and return it to our client as such.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "If a consumer simply asks not to be contacted via cell we will remove the cell and send a collection letter if it is within FDCPA guidelines.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "Other solutions may be to send a settlement letter allowing the consumer to save money in an effort to resolve the issue.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "The industry certainly didn't set a very good standard ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "and regulation is certainly needed.", "reasons": ["6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "I think the vast majotiry of us get the message loud and clear and are making sure we comply impicitly.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "policy", "text": "The effort needs to be two fold.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "policy", "text": "The consumers have to be willing to discuss the accounts and express willingness to pay.", "reasons": ["11"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "After all, if everyone's debts were paid, there would be no need for a call.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "value", "text": "And that's not meant to sound standoffish.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "value", "text": "The simple fact remains at the end of the day, debts are owed and our clients want their money.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "policy", "text": "Consumers must share some of the responsibility.", "reasons": ["13"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1298", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Let's keep it as simple as possible. ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Based on 3rd party disclosure statue blocking the ID benifits the consumer.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "One never knows who is at the other end of the phone.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "375", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Possibly the most egregious action of all regarding credit card debt occurred in 2002, suspiciously close to the 911 aftermath.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "While insurance companies were paying out tens of millions of dollars to building owners who suffered damage because of 911 ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "(which technically they should not have done ", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "since this was an act of war which is NOT covered by most insurance plans), ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "the comptroller of the currency was DENYING insurance companies from competing with credit card companies in the credit card debt suspension insurance arena.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "The result was a credit card debt suspension insurance monopoly for the credit card companies with premiums that were overpriced by a factor of 1000% to 2000%", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "fact", "text": "The profit margin was so high for credit card debt suspension insurance that the CFPB actually had to fine the credit card companies OVER 500 MILLION DOLLARS in the summer of 2012 for overly aggressive credit card debt suspension insurance sales and marketing practices.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "I had warned about overpriced credit card debt suspension insurance back in 2008 with the creation of www.credit-protector.com", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "but was never compensated for my efforts.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "fact", "text": "It meant that MOST credit card defaults in the United States over the last 10 to 15 years were based on a fraudulent foundation of obscenely over priced credit card debt suspension insurance that consumers could not afford to keep purchasing.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "fact", "text": "Consumers were literally paying for 5 years worth of credit card debt suspension insurance but only receiving 3-5 months worth of coverage!", "reasons": ["9"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "Most of the times that a judge was declaring a credit card default, they were propping up the overpricing of a monopolistic credit card debt suspension insurance policy that did not fairly give consumers the most obvious way to protect themselves from a default that was caused by life changing event", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "value", "text": "We could literally fix the U.S. economy almost overnight by doing the right thing.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "policy", "text": "First acknowledge credit card debt suspension insurance fraud that the credit card companies have perpetrated on the american people over the past 10 to 15 years ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "policy", "text": "and as retribution reduce all consumer credit card debt by approximately 65%.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 15, "type": "policy", "text": "Then raise the monthly minimum payment on the remaining 35% from 2% to 5% ", "reasons": ["16"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 16, "type": "value", "text": "so the monthly payment remains roughly the same but consumers feel their debt more easily going forward.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 17, "type": "fact", "text": "The comptroller of the currency tried to get credit card companies to raise their monthly minimum payment requirements from 2% to 4 or 5% back around 2005 but relented when it became obvious too many people would default.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 18, "type": "fact", "text": "By reducing consumer credit card debt by 65% as a form of reparations for debt suspension insurance fraud consumers suddenly have a lot less debt BUT still have to make a similar monthly payments.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 19, "type": "fact", "text": "However MORE of that monthly payment goes towards paying down the actual debt rather than the cesspool known as ever expanding interest rate charges.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "649", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "The majority of the time, when a debt has been paid off, it has been paid to the client, not the collection agency.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "Most of that time when that debt has been paid to the client, the client neglects to report it to the agency.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "So the collectors continue to call on a paid debt that they have no knowledge of.", "reasons": ["0_1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "It's really not the collectors fault, it is generally the client's.", "reasons": ["0_1"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "477", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "If a consumer states that he disputes the debt, the debt collector should immediately cease ALL collection activity until the debt is validated.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "And, by validation, it needs to be more than \"the name and social security information matches the creditor's records.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "The validation process should include a clear and complete copy of ALL DOCUMENTS that create the alleged obligation.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "If none is available, then the debt should be cancelled.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "482", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "another issue is an original business which isn't covered under FDCPA only needs a servicemember's military address (usually their only address),", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "they simple replace the servicemember/customer's name with Commanding Officer on a mailing or use a unit locator and ask for Commanding Officer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Considering some of the businesses located outside of a base that prey on unsophisticated young troops, like a used car lot and it's easy to have more leverage with that troop.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "663", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "Payment processor Visa has general information and the corresponding state statutes about the 10 states that prohibit companies from charging credit/debit card fees located on their website.", "reasons": null, "evidence": ["3", "4"]}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Texas, which most people would think would be business friendly, is actually really consumer friendly when it comes to these fees, for example.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "Texas has had a long-standing state law against credit card fees, and just recently this year created a new state law to cover against debit card fees and other stored value cards (like prepaid debit cards).", "reasons": null, "evidence": ["5", "6"]}, {"id": 3, "type": "reference", "text": "http://usa.visa.com/personal/using_visa/checkout_fees/", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "reference", "text": "http://usa.visa.com/download/merchants/surcharging-faq-by-merchants.pdf", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "reference", "text": "http://www.statutes.legis.state.tx.us/Docs/FI/htm/FI.339.htm", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "reference", "text": "http://www.capitol.state.tx.us/tlodocs/83R/billtext/html/HB03068F.htm", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "And, no, I do not have any knowledge of if debt collectors are charging debtors payment processing fees or not,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "policy", "text": "but if they are--especially in the states that forbid this practice--they should not be allowed to do so.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "policy", "text": "And I further believe that in the remaining states that do not have any laws forbidding credit/debit cards surcharges, that a fed reg/law should forbid debt collectors in all states from doing so.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1001", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have one debt in the court.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "Here is my issue, I never received any paperwork saying there was a court date.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "I did receive a letter from my bank a month after the court hearing saying they received a garnishment notice.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "They could've saved the court costs since I already had told them I was unemployed.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "Secondly, after I received the bank letter, I then received three (that's right three) garnishment hearing notices from three different companies for the same debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "Since I was unemployed I could not afford to get an attorney.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "It would've been nice if I could have provided the court (telephonically or by pre-trial documents) with documentation to explain why I was unable to pay the debt, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "but the paperwork said to only respond if you did not owe the debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "policy", "text": "I believe court documents and debt companies should have easier and clearer paperwork for the lay person to understand their rights.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "policy", "text": "And yes, debt collectors should have to provide documentation that the debt is owed and they have the right to collect.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1385", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Notification that a debt is being sold would be ideal ", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "as it would afford the debtor the opportunity to negotiate the amount and possibly assist in thwarting any potential negative reporting on one's credit report.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "If a debtor is afforded the opportunity to negotiate his or her debt for a reasonable amount, perhaps the selling and reselling of debt may be marginalized.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "More and more consumers have emails and other modes of communication", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "and therefore, it would be in the best interest of all parties to amicably resolve issues.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "However, should the dispute not be quelled, reasonable arrangements should be afforded to the debtor.", "reasons": ["6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "Debts as assets is an outrageous concept ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "and it behooves both the debtor and the creditor to \"work-it-out\".", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "That is in the best interest of all.", "reasons": ["9"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "It begins with information, communication and resolution.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "779", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I had the same situation with another cellular carrier.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "It seems it's a ploy to keep making the debt seem fresh.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "It was another early termination fee,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "and I wrote many letters before it was finally removed from my credit report.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "I think that the tactic of selling the same debt to keep it on a credit report definitely should stop.", "reasons": ["5_6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "It is one debt,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "fact", "text": "and there is a time limit for how long it stays on one's credit report.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "One way to keep track of this is to require people to be notified if a debt is sold.", "reasons": ["8", "9"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "fact", "text": "It is required when a mortgage is sold.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "It seems like a no-brainer.", "reasons": ["8"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "policy", "text": "The rules should also be written to discourage -- no, to bar -- collections companies from passing around debt for the purpose of keeping it on credit reports.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "691", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "From a creditor's standpoint, I generally agree with this comment.", "reasons": ["1", "2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "I think a good validation notice could answer a lot of the consumer's question.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "I think the author of the above note had some very well reasoned thoughts.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "I wouldn't go so far as to add that an itemized statement must be provided, particularly if one might not be available (perhaps because of record retention rules or because one simply may not exist),", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "but providing information as to the type of account, brand name of the original creditor issuing the account, the account number, the date of last pay, and the name of the party from whom the debt may have been purchased would help.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "Providing documentation at the get go seems rather unneccessary and costly, particularly if the wording of the letter allows the consumer to readily identify the account, and the disclosures allow the consumer to request documentation for validation.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "668", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I have found, on numerous occasions, that the debt collection process allowing firms purchasing debt - for pennies on the dollar - often use intimidating tactics that can easily be considered extortion.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "Every time a deb t collector purchases an old, out-of-date debt, they re-file the debt with the credit bureau(s).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "This continues the credit report damage for years - sometimes decades.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "As a mortgage banker, those persons often find it impossible to secure a mortgage and realize the American dream of home ownership.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1395", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "What Nancy H said exemplifies the problem: no standards across the board.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "What happens to you in this situation depends on the collection agency, the creditor (in the first place) and where you live.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "Where you live should not be a factor.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "932", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "The contractor was just able to make up an invoice and send it to the collection agency.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "At the time legal action was being pursued against the contractor ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "and we then had to deal with collection agencies aswell as a unlicensed contractor.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "So in answer to your question , I dont think it would have made much difference", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "as it appears that an invoice is sufficient grounds to file a claim", "reasons": ["0_1"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "318", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Agree with RBell.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Delinquent borrowers already almost always know they're delinquent", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "so further notices are not productive.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "When notices are provided they should include the name of the original account holder and the full account number to establish a connection between any tier debt collector and the original account holder.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "907", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "that wouldn't be very efficient.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "The FCRA does not allow reporting of a debt that is no longer being serviced by a creditor/collector.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "For example, if your creditor is currently reporting the debt but sells it to a debt collector, your creditor can no longer report on that debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "The buyer can, if he subjects himself to the corresponding federal regulation.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "426", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "As someone who regularly reviews credit reports,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "I am appalled by a practice I see regularly.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "Debt Collectors frequently resubmit the report of a debt as delinquent every month .", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "This will have a highly adverse impact on the consumer's credit scores.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "324", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Why should, an agency have to mail a letter to the consumer who requested not to be called?", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "They most likely won't read it", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "771", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "Well, I get at least one call per week from a litigant saying \"I was served with a summons today, and it says I must appear within 10 (or 30) days to answer this complaint, but there is no court date on the papers for me to appear\",", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "and I have to tell them the procedure (and point out to them the blurb about you not physically having to come to court to answer).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "I'm not sure how much clearer the wording in the summons has to be,", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "I understand them fully, and not just because I'm familiar with the forms,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "I'm just smarter than the average litigant I have to deal with I guess.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "The complaints do state that they have the rights to the debt, under verification that is notarized, at first...", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "fact", "text": "but they cannot enter the default judgment unless they provide the affidavit signed by both parties who owned and now owns the debt, which is generally attached to their judgments.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "886", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "Keep in mind that there are businesses or entities that allow people to receive credit for things they do not have money for at the moment.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "The business or entity, in good faith, extends credit to the consumer with the intent to receive payment at a later date.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "The business or entity was provided contact information by the consumer that it will use to collect or pass along to a collection agency to use to collect.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "The consumer can list whatever numbers or information they want ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "and the business or entity must consider it to be truthful.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "Often the only way to determine if the information is accurate is to make a phone call.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "I've received these calls myself.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "Depending on how much debt and how many business or entities have extended credit may be a factor on how often third parties are contacted.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "I do believe that collection agencies that violate the law are not good for anyone.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "testimony", "text": "However, I pay my bills", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "and would expect that everyone should be responsible for paying their bills.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "Much of the discussion has nothing to do with weather the bill is owed but how the contact was made.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1066", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I have a fairly common last name,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "and my listing in the phone book uses two initials rather than a first name.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "I get calls from credit collectors several times a week looking for various people with my last name and one or the other of my two initials.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "They are just taking a stab in the dark.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "When I tell them that I don't live with any other family members and that I have an excellent credit rating, they take me off of their list to of numbers for today's person of interest.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "When I ask them not to call me at all because I have no other people living with me that they would be looking for, they say that they only had me listed for their person of the day.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "Tomorrow my number might pop up as a possibility for tomorrow's person of the day, but they \"can't do anything about tomorrow.\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "I actually had a credit collection rep (in India) say that to me.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "813", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I have a lot of concerns with emails.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "Email clients have privacy/security settings that do not allow the sender to know if/when an email has been or was received.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "The problem is that even with these privacy/security settings, senders are able to get around these settings.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "This is widely used by spammers and hackers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "All of the spam experts all say not to open emails that are spam or potential spam, ", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "because the spammers are so good at manipulating and getting around the privacy/security settings and force the recipients email client to inform the sender of when/if an email was opened.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "Also, I do not like the idea that collectors can insert links in emails.", "reasons": ["7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "The more unscrupulous collectors and unscrupulous employees can insert links that are harmful to the security of the user\"s computers and offensive to the recipients (like pornographic material).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "policy", "text": "Just think about how many collectors still (even after all of the lawsuits) use offensive and abusive language over the telephone,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "policy", "text": "just think about what kind of harm these bad apples would be able to do with emails.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "I also I do not like the emails ", "reasons": ["11"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "because of the ease with which collection companies can sell the email lists to marketers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "testimony", "text": "Many decades ago, one of my neighbors was a debt collector.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "testimony", "text": "She would tell me that if they couldn't get money out of the debtors then we make money off of them by selling your address and personal information to marketing companies.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "value", "text": "I have huge concerns for allowing collectors from using emails.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 15, "type": "policy", "text": "Any rules that allow collectors to use email should come with deliberate care and attention to the privacy/security, materials and content, and the restriction of selling email lists.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 16, "type": "value", "text": "I also worry about true and accurate identification of emails.", "reasons": ["17"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 17, "type": "fact", "text": "Spammers/hackers are able to manipulate how emails are presented and the name of the email address that they send with.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 18, "type": "policy", "text": "there should also be rules restricting collectors are manipulating and spoofing their email addresses.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1265", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I believe all of the possibilities listed are necessary.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I never did business with Joe's Collection Agency and would never recognize any debt they allege is owed.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Interest and other fees would make the amounts unrecognizable either even in the event I could miraculously determine that $757.24 is an old utility bill.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1355", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "The debt collector must be required to submit the original application for credit with the consumer's original signature and the original letter of approval for the credit.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "The debt collection company should be required to submit full documentation that the debt actually exists.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Too many debt collectors rely on falsified affidavits.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "308", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "Debt collectors continuously resell the debt to other debt collectors who start the clock all over again.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "Then that debt collector resells the debt ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "and the 3rd debt collector restarts the clock again, and so on.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "The burden of proof is put on the consumer to prove it is an old debt.", "reasons": ["4", "5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "The credit reporting agencies don't automatically remove old debts ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "nor do they check to see if a newly reported debt is in fact a 9 year old debt that has been resold numerous times.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "The credit agencies (CRA) are more of a problem for consumers than the debt collectors.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "fact", "text": "The CRAs are paid by the credit card companies", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "fact", "text": "and the credit card companies have bigger profits when they can charge higher rates based on poor credit scores.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "So there is inherently a huge conflict of interest here.", "reasons": ["7_8"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "If the CRAs can keep our credit scores down the card companies can make more money and don't mind paying the CRAs a piece of the action.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "Seems like unspoken collusion to me.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "684", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "The state in which I practice does not allow jurisdiction based solely on where the contract was signed.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "As such, we limit our filings to the venues where we reasonably believe the consumer resides.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "The states typically define what is the proper court thereafter, whether its based on amount, location, etc.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "so even if there is a large judicial districts we do not have the choice to file elsewhere by local rules.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "637", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I can state from personal experience that when our savings ran out I became eligible for in home support services ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "in which I as an unpaid caregiver could be paid a very modest amount (at minimum wage payment) ", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "because I was a caregiver.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "By being an in home CareGiver, I was saving the state a lot more money than it would cost to pay me a small amount every month via in home support services.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "I told this to all of my creditors, none of them cared.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "Then reality hit, my state agency that was supposed to help me obtain in home support services instead cast fear into both me and my parent by stating to me on the phone that whatever they paid me, they would file a lien on the home to get back if I outlived my parent.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "It turns out this application of the law did not apply to me.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "However the damage was done.", "reasons": null, "evidence": ["8"]}, {"id": 8, "type": "testimony", "text": "I lost 1.75 years of eligibility and probably enough money to pay all of my vendors, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "and, I would have never had to prolong the default for more than a couple of months if any of my vendors had cared enough to just help me get through the process of applying for in home support services.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "But because judges have become so vindictive in their approach to credit card defaulters, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "judges have allowed the credit card companies to become LAZY at solving their own problems internally.", "reasons": ["10"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "value", "text": "Nobody helps, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "value", "text": "everybody simply self protects their own interests first and foremost.", "reasons": ["12"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "843", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I made a comment below and would like to know how to make them stop calling me for my deadbeat kids debt.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I tell them either I will pass on the info or that I have no contact info for them.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "Only one collector took me off their list.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "I am still being harrassed by 10 others.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "I am being forced to drop my land line which I have had for 40 years to get away from them.", "reasons": ["2", "3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "It really bugs me ", "reasons": ["6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "because I have a near perfect score of 797 .", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "903", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "E-Oscar was created by the credit reporting agencies due to a requirement that is outlined in the Fair Credit Reporting Act.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "This process is fully electronic save for the consumer's ability to upload paper correspondence or documents for the debt collector/creditor to review.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "Additionally, the CFPB has published clarification as to the requirements surrounding a \"reasonable investigation\" when a dispute is issued, requiring debt collectors/creditors to go one step further.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "The underlying issue is this system is abused by many individuals who mass submit disputes repeatedly that have no validity.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "Agencies and creditors are forced to sift through all of those frivolous disputes in order to actually address legitimate disputes.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "514", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Please go hard after the service industry.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "They have done a lot to foul up the debt collection process by having their service people FALSE SERVE and FALSE SUBSERVE prospective debt collection alleged defaulters.", "reasons": null, "evidence": ["2_6"]}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "It's happened to me twice, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "the first time the process server simply guessed by using the most generic age size, weight and assign a made up name!", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "The second time the servicer simply called the sub server \"Jane Doe\" and once again made up the most generic cut across as many age, height and race descriptions they could come up with, which meant they could not be more far off.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "Then when I went to court I just happened to hear another defendant make the claim to the judge that they were never served, that the paper work was left outside the door.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "Besides the service company lying in court documents about serving someone that was not actually served, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "policy", "text": "which in and of itself should be enough to give the judge some type of latitude to do something to protect the defendants, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "when a debt collector knows they can get a false service, they have MUCH LESS MOTIVATION to negotiate with the defendant. ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "Judges don't seem to get this aspect of false service.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "testimony", "text": "I know what I know ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "testimony", "text": "and I will state unequivocally anywhere that I have twice been false served/subserved.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1158", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "There's nothing in place for any of them, unless (often several years down the road) a judge decides to throw them out.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "This is yet another consequence of the litigious society in which we currently live.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "I don't have the answers,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "but it seems that someone in government or law should be able to do something about unscrupulous attorneys who create a claim out of thin air just to make a buck.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "839", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "If you put an article about landlords and illegal lawsuits and collections, you would be flooded with responses.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "It is an area of collections that is hidden from you but very prevalent in NYC.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "814", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "If emails are allowed, they should not be allowed to be sent outside of what is the acceptable time for phone calls.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "I would like to restrict the time to inside normal business hours for the locale of the debtor,", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "because no business email should ever be sent from the office outside normal business hours.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "This is basic and normal business etiquette for emails.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "But a compromise could be made for what is accepted for phone calls.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "However, I would like to see no emails sent on Sundays.", "reasons": ["6_7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "fact", "text": "The USPS does not operate on Sundays", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "policy", "text": "and neither should emails of a business nature.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1282", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "They will just continue to call.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "Not answering does not stop the constant calls.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "They need to be required to identify themselves accurately ", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "so the consumer has at least a fighting chance to speak with them.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "In my case I have no debts of my own but am constantly harassed for other people's debts ", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "because I have a fairly common last name.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "fact", "text": "They just start calling everyone with the same last name as their actual debtor.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1022", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I think the issue you have identified here in this post is key - lack of financial literacy.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "So many people borrow money without reading contracts, without understanding the law, without considering the risks.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "We live in a society centered on immediate gratification, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "where people who can't afford things just charge them, thinking they'll pay it back later.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "But then something happens - a job loss, medical issues, unexpected expenses.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "So few people even maintain sufficient savings accounts these days, or put money away for retirement.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "If we really want to get to the heart of this issue, it has to start with education, and financial literacy.", "reasons": ["2_5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "Now, I'm not saying the banks and lenders are innocent participants", "reasons": ["8"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "they have certainly taken advantage of the \"instant gratification\" mindset by extending credit with high interest rates and fees, knowing that someone somewhere will sign up for it.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "But they can't bear the brunt of the blame for societal ignorance.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "535", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "Look, its 2013!", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Ignoring phone calls is annoying ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "and constantly seeing missed calls is aggrivating.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Why are bill collectors stuck in ancient times?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "Text me!! ", "reasons": ["6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "Email me!!", "reasons": ["6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "Those phone calls are not going to be answered ", "reasons": ["7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "because I work and have kids.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "Communicati g with them would be so much easier if I could text and email these people.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "fact", "text": "Seriously this is not 1950 we live in!!", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1171", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "One issue I am experiencing is that since I allegedly received an overpayment of wages from a former employer,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have NONE of the consumer protections that I should.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "I fall into the gray space of being a consumer", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "and my alleged (and incorrectly so) debt is considered \"commercial\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "and therefore there are absolutely NO regulations on the activities of the debt collector.", "reasons": ["2", "3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "The individual assigned to my account has repeatedly revealed to a third party that he is trying to collect a debt from me.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "The alleged debt has never been substantiated,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "588", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "The name of the agency is the CONSUMER Financial Protection Bureau not the Collector Financial Protection Bureau.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "The industry have their lobbyists ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "and consumers have the CFPB.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "The goal is to protect consumers from illegal practices by certain industries ", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "and that sometimes means more regulations.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "230", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "FDCPA should define what constitutes reasonable period of time.", "reasons": ["1_3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "In my experience most attorneys who represent a debtor do not return communication inquiries about representation.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "In most cases the delay in response may be caused by the debtor paying installment payments to the attorney to file a bankruptcy proceeding.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "When the debtor does not keep the repayment terms a creditor is presently not notified that the representation has terminated ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "and there is no attorney representation.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1017", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I don't understand, Mr. Bartmann", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "you believe creditors should just wait until consumers feel like they can afford to pay?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "What if that takes years?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "Litigation preserves the creditor's right to recover the money owed and allows it to be collected later, when the consumer is able to do so.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "If litigation cannot be used to enforce creditors' rights, the debt could become uncollectable in as little as three years.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "As noted by another commentator, this will most certainly have a negative impact on the economy and the cost of credit ", "reasons": ["6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "because it will drive up prices to cover that risk.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "It will also make obtaining credit next to impossible for high-risk individuals.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "385", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "First, a third party collecting on behalf of a lender isn't, nor should be, defined as a furnisher of information.", "reasons": ["1_3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "While the FDCPA requires notice specific to the validity of the debt, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "the FCRA has requirements for users of consumer reports.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Combining two statue requirements in the initial notice of a debt serves no purpose.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "Sending during the 30 day notice would create confusion in the event the consumer responds, for example, to the validity of the debt and does not include a request about a credit report accuracy.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "I believe the issue is whether a third party debt collector or debt buyer should report an account to a credit reporting agency which would overlap the original lender's last report on the consumer account.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "In my opinion they should not.", "reasons": ["7", "8"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "I have seen confusion due to lack of rule clarity.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "For example, if a consumer files a bankruptcy petition who should report that event?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "If a third party opts to report then the third party would be required to report events that take place during or after the bankruptcy filing.", "reasons": ["10"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "fact", "text": "To date, Title 11 offers no direction to reporting and neither does the FCRA other than a credit reporting agency removing after 10 years.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1150", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I guess I should also have clarified in my previous comment that I have made attempts to deal with creditors directly if I know who they are and who they claim to be representing", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "but my personal perception is they PREFER to continue contacting 3rd parties", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "because they hope I'll just pay them to avoid the public humiliation.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "And in regards to a comment I read here that creditors can call a 3rd party again if they have a reasonable belief that the person knows how to contact the debtor, I disagree with that entirely.", "reasons": ["4", "8"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "First of all, I'm not aware of any law that compels a 3rd party to provide current contact information for a debtor,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "so even if they do know where that debtor is, they don't deserve to be harassed daily for months or years as punishment for not offering up that information.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "fact", "text": "Many people don't want to be involved", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "fact", "text": "and no law that I know of says they have to if they aren't a party to the debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "Secondly, there is no clear and concise way I know of that a creditor can prove what was a reasonable belief.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "testimony", "text": "My in-laws have no idea how to reach my sister-in-law", "reasons": ["10"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "because she wants it that way.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "testimony", "text": "They haven't spoken in 3 years", "reasons": ["9"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "value", "text": "and I don't see that changing.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "value", "text": "You can't assume that certain relatives MUST know where a debtor is.", "reasons": ["9"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1059", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I was receiving 4 or 5 calls a day from Midland Debt Collection daily for two weeks on my cellphone.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "As I'm unemployed and scraping by I was ignoring - or rather trying to ignore - the calls.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "They were always hang-ups.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "Never any message.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "As I live in Indiana - a \"business-oriented\" state, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "it seems the laws favor the debt collectors over the debtors.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "Limits on calls? Please, do.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "When I finally did have the gumption to answer when they called at 8:10am on a Sunday morning, I made a strong case about being harrassed and informed him I didn't want to be contacted on my cell phone.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "testimony", "text": "It's only a few days but I'll see.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "testimony", "text": "I still don't know if it was any legit debt that they were calling about.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1002", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "About a month after my husband left the military and before we even moved into a new place, a creditor called his parents and told them he was in the military with my husband and had papers that hadn't been signed so he had to get in touch with him.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "My mother-in-law knew we didn't have a phone yet, so because she thought it was something urgent she gave him our friends number.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "That collector called the friends number told the friend he was collecting a debt and my husband (not knowing what was told or how he got the number) let the collector know we had just moved and the payment was an oversight.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "Of course, the collector was trying very hard to get new address, phone, employer, etc but we did not have that yet.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "The bill was paid, yet they continued to call his parents and the friend after they had new contact info for him.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "Keep in mind, this was over a late $10 payment.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "I understand they are trying to collect a debt ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "policy", "text": "but doing so by false statements and telling others of the debt should never be allowed.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "policy", "text": "Shouldn't they just be allowed to leave a name and contact number?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "541", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I dont mind the spouse.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "I mean shes my wife ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "so I dont see why not.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "But I dont agree with girlfriends or boyfriends for those who dont have a spouse.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "Spouse is okay.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1365", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I do not agree, when it come to company call or text all day and night.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "New federal rule should not do this at all.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "It sound like somebody is getting pay to put this new federal laws.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "It all about money as always", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "395", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Unscrupulous debt collectors use this tactic trying to force people into agreeing to repay a debt.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "The threat of debt collection calls at work is a powerful incentive to repay a debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1384", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I agree. ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "However, I believe that having a universal or national statute of limitations would alleviate this problem.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "The current system is too confusing.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "526", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I dont understand why bill collectors are so stuck in ancient times.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "I get so many calls and its annoying.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "I would much rather get a text or email.", "reasons": ["3", "4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "The phone ringing can be annoying and a text is more subtle.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "It also doesnt require me to hear a long dragging voicemail.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "I would rather get a text saying who they are and what they want.", "reasons": ["3", "4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "If I dont respond soon then call me.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1313", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Here's what the federal government laws should mandate how the collection companies and CRAs should investigate disputes", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "All collection actions and reporting actions should stop immediately.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "The time line should be equal on the consumer,collection company,CRAs reporting period.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "The original debt owner or collection company that purchase the account, should produce the original copy of the signed contract, court documents, and any verifiable records relating to the dispute.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "Forward those documents to the disputing party within the set aside timeline.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "Any and all verification letters would have to state and indicate such findings.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "Once the dispute could not be verified by,name,social,signed document copy of original agreement, it should be immediately deleted.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "The collections companies and original debt owners are responsible for the validity of information they get,buy,receive,send or share.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "policy", "text": "So, if they buy good or bad debt they should be held responsible.", "reasons": ["7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "policy", "text": "The number,types,unclear,clear,collections disputes should all be investigated the same", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1321", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I had to spend quite a bit of time dealing with their repeated calls.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "Of course, they weren't looking for me but rather for someone with my very common last name and first initial.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "I had many calls from them one day.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "Apparently, their telephone representatives were trained to hang up if they received any response other than, \"How do I pay?\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "They'd hang up on me before I could complete a sentence.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "That particular day, either by accident or through malice (I suspect the latter.),", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "they had their robo dialer programmed to call back immediately.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "The representative would hang up on me ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "testimony", "text": "and before I could step away from the phone, the robo dialer would call me back ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "testimony", "text": "and I'd be speaking with another representative who would hang up on me.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "testimony", "text": "After many such calls and hang-ups, I was finally able to get a representative to stay on the line with me long enough for me to explain that they were calling the wrong person.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "testimony", "text": "After that the calls stopped.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "value", "text": "As I think back on this experience, I find it quite comical, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "value", "text": "but I didn't at the time.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "testimony", "text": "I did file complaints with the FTC and my state's Attorney General.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1110", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Given the highly coercive consequences of having negative information reported to or by CRAs on consumer credit reports, I think it is reasonable that a debt not be deemed \"verified\" or \"substantiated\" unless and until there's a final non-appealable order, but only in circumstances where the consumer has timely disputed the existence or the amount of the debt.", "reasons": ["7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "Currently, if you dispute a debt, the debt collector reports you to the CRAs ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "and your credit standing is adversely impacted; i.e., the damage is already done at that point.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "In other words, the notation on the credit report that the debt is disputed by the consumer is largely ignored by potential lenders, employers, landlords, etc.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "Thus, disputing the debt does nothing to prevent harm to the consumer.", "reasons": ["1", "3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "The debt collector and creditor threaten to report you to the CRAs as a coercive tactic to force you to pay a debt", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "even though you might legitimately not owe the debt or the amount claimed to be owed.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "As for my proposal, I do not think this will lead to more litigation. Just the opposite.", "reasons": ["8", "9_10"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "If a consumer doesn't timely dispute the debt, then the debt can be deemed verified or substantiated.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "If, however, the debt is timely disputed, creditors and debt collectors will have to evaluate whether to initiate litigation and weigh the likelihood of prevailing at trial ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "and this may cause creditors and debt collectors to be more judicious about which debts to take to trial.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "This proposal would also protect consumers from having their credit standing negatively impacted until after it is conclusively determined that a purported debt that is disputed is in fact owed and the amount of such debt is conclusively determined.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "value", "text": "As an alternative to my initial proposal, a rule could be adopted that would impose significant statutory penalties, treble damanages and recovery of attorney's fees against creditors, debt collectors and CRAs in the event the consumer can prove either the disputed debt doesn't exist or the amount of the debt is less than that claimed to be owed.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "value", "text": "This approach, however, places the burden of proof on the consumer", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "policy", "text": "and I feel strongly that the burden of proof should be on the creditors and debt collectors to affirmatively prove the existence and amount of any disputed debt before a consumer's credit report is adversely impacted.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1390", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "That might work if each state had reasonable, intelligent and realistic collection rules.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "But just the fact that the cost of getting a report varies wildly shows such disparities from state to state.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "My opinion is that there desperately needs to be some uniformity.", "reasons": ["1", "3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "This would help people to know what is expected of them, and what to expect.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "703", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Sorry, but you are mistaken about debt collectors not being able to change information in your credit file.", "reasons": ["1", "2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "Yes, they can,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "and yes they do.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "If my account has been sold (several) times to other people, and my original creditor no longer owns the account, then how would my account be (updated/reported) by that company (debt collector) that purchased it?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "And, yes they (the person furnishing) the information to the credit bureau can and do supply credit bureaus with fraudulent information.", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "That's how Debt Collector's get sued in the first place.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "750", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Bonzarel. while I think your idea is a good one,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "it could open the floodgates to interest rate padding the debt until it reaches one of the \"floors\" that you are suggesting.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "30% interest rate charges, penalties and fees (which in turn also get hit with a 30% interest rate charge), can accelerate even a 500 dollar debt into the thousands in less than 24 months time.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1068", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "I would like to see a rule prohibiting debt collectors, debt owners/debt buyers, and other related affiliates from being able to pull a debtor\"s credit report once the debt is officially time-barred and out of SOL.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "I would also like there to be a rule that specifically distinguishes between a \"hard pull\" and a \"soft pull\" credit inquiry.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have been opted out of promotional marketing via the www.optoutprescreen.com website for years.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "I do not have debt and have never had debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "What I do have is a common name, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "and so from time to time I will have various debt collectors and debt buyers \"soft pulling\" my credit reports while they are trying to locate whomever they are trying to locate.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "This should not be allowed even if the debt is still collectable and within the SOL.", "reasons": ["7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "fact", "text": "No debt collector has a \"permissible purpose\" to just randomly \"soft pull\" my credit reports just because I have a common name.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "policy", "text": "As far as being outside the SOL and time-barred debts: no debt collector and debt owners/debt buyers should be allowed to pull someone\"s credit report ", "reasons": ["10", "9"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "fact", "text": "since they can't legally sue the debtor outside of the SOL.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "So there is no need to continue pulling someone\"s credit report.", "reasons": ["9"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "policy", "text": "As far as the \"hard pull\" \"soft pull\" is concerned: There needs to be specific language that prohibits any debt collectors, debt owners/debt buyers, and other related affiliates from performing \"hard pull\" credit report inquiries.", "reasons": ["12"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "value", "text": "The FCRA makes it clear what \"permissible purposes\" are ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "fact", "text": "but it does not specifically state or distinguish between a \"hard pull\" and a \"soft pull\" credit inquiry.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "fact", "text": "A \"hard pull\" is a consumer-initiated request for an extension of credit.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 15, "type": "fact", "text": "Anything other than a consumer-initiated request is a \"soft pull.\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 16, "type": "testimony", "text": "But time and time again, I have friends, family members, and online forum members, tell me and show me that a debt collector or a debt owner/debt buyer has \"hard pulled\" their credit report.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 17, "type": "testimony", "text": "And some of these times are when the debt is time-barred from being outside the SOL and also from the Credit Reporting Time Period.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 18, "type": "value", "text": "This is unacceptable.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 19, "type": "fact", "text": "A \"hard pull\" will decrease a consumers credit score and will be visible for up to 25 months to anyone who does have a legitimate permissible purpose to view that consumer\"s credit report", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 20, "type": "fact", "text": "Making a \"hard pull\" on a debtor\"s credit report could be a violation of the FDCPA in the privacy of the debtor.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 21, "type": "policy", "text": "Any debt collectors, debt owners/debt buyers, and other related affiliates should be prohibited from doing \"hard pulls\" ", "reasons": ["19", "20"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 22, "type": "policy", "text": "and the CFPB should make it absolutely clear.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 23, "type": "reference", "text": "<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.optoutprescreen.com\">www.optoutprescreen.com</a>", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "458", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Any form of written communication should count as a notice in writing.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "If a debt collector receives a notice via email of contact they should be required to follow it.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1289", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Calls to the workplace should not be permitted at all.", "reasons": ["1", "2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "Harassing the consumer at his her/workplace can come to the attention of the employer and get the consumer fired or limit advancement.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "The collector then does not get paid because of the collector's own egregious conduct.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1211", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I too have received calls from collectors who are on fishing expeditions, looking for a person who owes money.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "THE PROBLEM IS, EVEN AFTER BEING INFORMED THAT THE PERSON THEY ARE LOOKING FOR CANNOT BE REACHED AT MY PHONE NUMER AND TO PUT ME ON THEIR DO NOT CALL LIST - THEY STILL CALL.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have contacted local law enforcement, state attorney general and federal levels and been informed that if I owed money, I can have the debt collector contact me in writing only, but if I don't owe money, I have no protection because the debt collector has a right to do business.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "Unless the debt collector has more than a last name that matches the person's who owes the debt, they should be allowed to attempt to contact that phone number ONLY until they are told that that person cannot be reached at that phone number.", "reasons": ["0_1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "They should need to have more than a last name for any further phone calls.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "They should also have to tell the person they insist on calling why they believe they can find the person who owes the money there.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "Additionally, they should also be required to inform the consumer of how to file a complaint if the calls continue.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "policy", "text": "There should be a penalty for harassing people who don't owe money.", "reasons": ["8"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "When you don't owe money, getting phone calls early in the morning or late at night twice a week is harassment", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "fact", "text": "the more abusive ones robo call several times a day and hang up when an answering machine picks up).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "policy", "text": "Additionally, the means of protecting yourself from harassment should not require any financial burden to the consumer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "testimony", "text": "I was told I could file a lawsuit in the case of one extremely abusive collector", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "980", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have the same exact problem.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have had this problem for 20+ years.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "I can't tell you how many times I've told the person on the other end that the person they are looking for has NEVER lived here and not a relative.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "It sure is disgusting.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "I can't figure out what to do.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "597", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have received calls from debt collectors at 9:30 pm,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "and I consider this rude.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have also had robocalls early in the morning that woke me up.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "I am 69 yrs old, and retired, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "and I sleep late.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "My health is not good at the moment, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "so sometimes I have had a bad night", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "policy", "text": "please, please don't wake me up with a robocall.", "reasons": ["3", "5"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1071", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "It is my companies practice to send a validation of debt notice to nearly all accounts placed.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "This is not required but a best practice.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "I also believe in most cases the original creditor provides notices to the consumer on their bill if they are going to be referred to collections.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "Also it is time to be realistic.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "Is it possible that a consumer is not notified of a transfer to collections? ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "Yes.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "fact", "text": "But that being said most if not all consumers know they have not paid their bill beyond 30 days and they could be sent to collections.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "policy", "text": "It is time personal responsibility plaid a part in rule making and that the rules apply to the vast majority of circumstances instead of trying to account for the rare occurrences where the process does not work fully.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "571", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I agree that there documentation should always be provided.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Why would I pay a debt without absolute proof that it belongs to me?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "532", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "That is insane.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "My mom heard one when I was playing my voice messages at home.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "They should only disclose through texts.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "Texts arent something that will be heard by others.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "That long message saying they are collectors and trying to colleft a debt is ridiculous!!", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "503", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Creditors should be entitled to require consumers to provide them with a contact address and phone number and to provide updates while debts are outstanding.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "If consumers do not do so, it should be fair for creditors (and collectors) to skip-trace or to reach them at other numbers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "Collectors should not be allowed to make calls to work until they have made multiple attempts to contact a consumer at home.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1005", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Owing to the inherently non-private nature of the internet,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "NOTHING should be sent electronically.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "There is absolutely nothing wrong with continuing the use of the US Mail.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "However, the consumer should be free to allow the use of specific electronic communications, if they deem it proper.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "However, that should be specific;", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "so that a collector cannot use Facebook, twitter, etc; only the specified means.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1173", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I'm concerned that the proposed rules are just a back door to allow Director Cordray to find out about my special toy collection.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "He has sent me writings demanding my special toy collection,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "and I'm afraid that now that he's Director of the CFPB, he's using his power to come after my favorite toy, Mr. Longblack.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1035", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Where in the adhesion contract does it state that the credit card agreement, an allegedly \"unsecured\" form of debt, takes priority over every single other occurrence that might happen in a person's life?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Are the Philippine hurricane victims or even more recent Tornado victims in the midwest who lost their homes and their streets soon to become \"defaulters\" who are then subject to ongoing penalties, fees and interest rate charges while also having their credit scores damaged?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "The point of involuntary default is that an event occurred beyond one's control that has prevented them from making monthly payments of the amount they are required to make.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "Involuntary Default simply means the defaulter promises to pay back what they owed at the time of the default, and nothing more.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "I would suggest that the \"promise to pay\" tenet is constitutional violation of cruel and inhuman punishment ", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "because credit card companies literally lord over their customers without clearly mentioning their Godlike status at the time of the agreement.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "The correlation between cigarettes and credit cards are astounding.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "Isn't it time for a clear warning on credit card products that state the truth?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "Warning: Your promise to pay your credit card bill on a monthly basis is more important than any natural disaster or personal tragedy that may occur in your life.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "fact", "text": "By allowing credit card companies to not place the warning from above in a viewable context to all sign-ups, they gain monetarily while not revealing a basic contract tenet that should be revealed.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "Therefore the \"promise to pay\" has been arranged under a false pretense.", "reasons": ["9"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "772", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I was not the one with debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I was a mediator trying to help.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "The people with this situation sometimes ignore the first notice to them and don't ask for a validation letter.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Others, I believe, do not read it carefully and see they have a small window of time to dispute the claim.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "I think the original notice letter to the debtor should HIGHLIGHT the part about a validation letter.", "reasons": ["2", "3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "I also, think the original creditor should be required to help resolve disputes instead of debtors or third parties like me only being able to talk with the collection agency.", "reasons": ["6_7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "Probably 50% of the agencies I have dealt with do not follow existing regulations.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "Without penalties they never will.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "The few that are reasonable and follow the rules are a pleasure to deal with, as a third party.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1238", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "The Telephone Consumer Protection Act of 1991 (TCPA) was passed by the United States Congress in 1991 and signed into law by President George H. W. Bush as Public Law 102-243.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "It amended the Communications Act of 1934.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "The TCPA is codified as 47 U.S.C. 227.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "The TCPA restricts telephone solicitations (i.e., telemarketing) and the use of automated telephone equipment.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "The TCPA limits the use of automatic dialing systems, artificial or prerecorded voice messages, SMS text messages, and fax machines.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "It also specifies several technical requirements for fax machines, autodialers, and voice messaging systems\"principally with provisions requiring identification and contact information of the entity using the device to be contained in the message.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1340", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Some problems that debt collectors and buyers have with giving consumers this information arises in the field of Electronic Data Interchange.", "reasons": ["1", "3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "Here, not all debts, especially with interest are calculated the same way,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "and since there are fees, such as statutory attorneys fees, and court costs, which can be added to the balance, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "calculating the balance becomes cumbersome when the data is transferred among Trading Partners on a daily basis ", "reasons": ["2", "4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "because the data gets lost in translation over day-to-day lags.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "Computers don't think the same way people do", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "and what we think is a simple calculation is muddled when partial payments are added and the data is transmitted between parties.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "994", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "While not specifically addressed in this website, the current punishment for violations of the FDCPA are practically teethless.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "100 is of little consequence to most companies.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "The law show be changed to all ow a 7 year statute of limitations (it is currently one year) and a maximum penalty, payable to the plaintiff, of either $10,000 or $100,000 for each violation.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "427", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "If federal rules can be ignored by local/municipal/state laws then the federal laws are irrelevant.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "Consumer credit is recognized in all 50 states and internationally.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "As such these laws should be enforced by each state and lower courts and states and such should not be able to make laws that ignore of superseed federal law.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1178", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "When anyone makes a demand for payment from another party, it is incumbent on that person to produce the evidence to support such demand and not up to the second party to produce evidence that he is not liable for such alleged debt.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Otherwise, anyone can create trouble and misery for any person out of mischief, ill-intent or out to make some fast money for himself or even to defame the second party,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "as proper businesses are adverse to bad publicity.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "If the first party claims to represent a third party to collect debt for that third party, then the first party (collector) must produce evidence that he is authorized by the third party to collect a debt for the third party alone", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "because anyone can claim to represent any party in an attempt to defraud the innocent second party.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "346", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I can't comment on any of this,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "but it would seem appropriate for Federal law to establish a framework of requirements for states to meet.", "reasons": ["2", "3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "This would level the playing field for debtors and creditors in all states.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "and would provide an equal basis for states to proceed with adding or amending their own laws affecting debt collection lawsuits.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "520", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "After having a perfect payment history for 15 years, I had to across the board default on six accounts ", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "because I became an unpaid caregiver for my parents.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "However, before I ever defaulted, I contacted each account and explained what was going on.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "I would also like to note that five of the six accounts were still being paid down until I ran out of savings.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "I discovered the credit card companies HAVE NO INTAKE for potential defaulters.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "I consider a potential default division a cost of doing business that credit card companies have eschewed ", "reasons": ["6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "fact", "text": "because they have co-opted the courts to do all the work for them for a very nominal fee.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "My goal was simple, keep making monthly miniscule autopay payments on all six accounts in exchange for no harrassing phone calls so that I could concentrate on CareGiving AND modifying my self employment so that I could make something every month.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "testimony", "text": "Everyone refused, and the harrassing and MORE IMPORTANTLY REPETITIVE phone calls started.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "testimony", "text": "I ended up having to convert my land lines to 6 dollar a month cell phones, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "testimony", "text": "and then I rarely used them ", "reasons": ["11"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "testimony", "text": "because I could not afford the 20 cents a minute cost.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "value", "text": "In essence the credit card companies and debt collectors destroyed the best way I had to regenerate earnings while still being an unpaid CareGiver.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "value", "text": "And as Marlene so eloquently pointed out, an additional roadblock is the debt collectors ABSOLUTE REFUSAL to put any verbal agreement reached in writing!", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "327", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "I think it should be illegal or miss leading for a agency to change its caller id.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "You could easily look up a relatives number and use that.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "There should be a rule regarding a change in caller id.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "488", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "Many states have a judgement law where a consumer with over a certain amount of judgements may be terminated from employment.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Having a collector call at work just seems to be another way to break down a consumer and put them at a disadvantage.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "A friend has mentioned to me receiving collection calls at work for one of his employees where the collector identified himself as \"Officer\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "My friend told the collector never to call again and that it's illegal to impersonate law enforcement.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "Too many other stories that went to court for FDCPA violations of collector harassment at work even when the employer has told the collector not to call there again.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "604", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I would like to see the time frame for validation change.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "I, as a consumer, have 30 days from the date of the letter to dispute the debt,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "however, the collection agency can take as long as they want, even years, to get back to the consumer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "This practice is not only bad ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "but some charge interest on the debt, even though they don't call it that (fee's\"), all the time they are 'looking into it\".", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "If I have 30 day's they should have the same time frame to get back to me, period.", "reasons": ["3", "4"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1076", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "Collectors are not calling me repeatedly ", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "because they don't believe me.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "They are calling me repeatedly ", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "because there are so many people with the same last name as me and one of my initials.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "It is just as annoying to get frequent calls about different individuals as it is to get frequent calls about the same individual.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "334", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "In theory this seems like a reasonable policy,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "but how can collectors know where a debtor is if they are calling his or her cell phone?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "Knowingly calling third parties should be prohibited across the board.", "reasons": ["3", "4_5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "It is no one else's business what goes on between creditors and their debtors.", "reasons": ["4_5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "Calls to a person's boss or family can cause further financial and domestic problems,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "neither of which will help with getting the debt paid.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1236", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I do not think collectors would mind reimbursing consumers who are charged per call or per message.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "Add $5 for the hassle of getting the refund.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "Collectors should have a way to make contact with consumers who choose not to have a flat-rate telephone service.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Honest, respectful and open communication by all parties is the key to giving consumers enough information to identify and understand debts and come to workable resolutions for legitimate debts.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "It is also the key to stopping calls to wrong numbers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "Collectors who are not honest and respectful should be fined or lose their right to be licensed.", "reasons": ["3", "4"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1407", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I agree with you that being in debt is not a crime,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "however, if a debtor defaults on a debt they basically have no rights if they cannot afford an attorney ", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "as one will not be provided for them by the state.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Pro Se can easily become a mess ", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "as no one will actually help with the paperwork, ", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "even state funded pro se agencies are simply paid to show where to get the right papers, not to fill them out.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "633", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "A lot of excellent points made by MLegz13.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "My elderly parents needed help with day to day activities even if they were too proud to say anything.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "I stopped my award winning video business to be their CareGiver.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "Once the savings ran out, I had to default after 15 years of having a perfect credit card payment history.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "The debt collectors were constantly accusing me of being a \"refuse to pay\" even though I said I acknowledge the debt but had no income at the moment.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "It is this type of scenario that requires debts be frozen where they were at the time of default and in exchange the debtor agrees to pay off the debt, even if the initial monthly payments are just for a couple of dollars.", "reasons": ["6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "What this does is free the debtor's phone lines so they can completely focus on moving forward rather than engage in pointless rat a tat with repetitive debt collection callers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "It's why I started the Debt Neutrality Petition as well.", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "policy", "text": "If you click on the link PLEASE read the comments left by some of the 500 plus people who have signed the petition.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "fact", "text": "Even a debt collector signed the petition, their comment speaks volumes of truth, as did all the others as well.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "reference", "text": "<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.change.org/petitions/congress-create-debt-neutrality-rights-for-paying-down-credit-cards-student-loans\">Debt Neutrality Petition.</a>", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "481", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "It seems that just about anyone can create a debt collection company", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "and if the owners and/or employees have unscrupulous desires, then it seems that privacy is a big concern.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Plus, if anyone can create/own debt collection companies, then it doesn't seem to surprise me why so many debt collecting companies break the laws.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "There should be tighter laws on the formation of debt collection companies and the employees that they can hire.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1098", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "I think the \"unless\" part of the rule about contacting a person more than once should be scrapped.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "They should not be allowed to contact anyone (other than the debtor him/herself) more than once.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "If the person (usually the innocent family member) they contact to try to locate the debtor is willing to give out contact info, fine.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "If not, whether they have it or not is beside the point.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "They should not be forced in the middle.", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "It is not their debt, or in any way their responsibility.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "And when collectors claim they can't give their name or a return phone number to be passed on because of privacy reasons, how can they expect someone else to share personal contact info with a stranger?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "816", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "Debtors often respond with \"I don't owe anything\",", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "which is vague and makes it harder to cater for their needs.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "If any rule making is needed, it is about the types of disputes a debtor may bring forth and the documentation needed for both the substantiation of that dispute", "reasons": ["0_1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "leaving the option for a dispute to be deemed frivolous", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "and what constitutes satisfaction of the dispute or proper proof.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "Otherwise, this is left for negotiation between individual collectors and debtors.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1179", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Validation should be obtained from the Creditor by the Collection Agency prior to any Collection attempt is made by the Collection Agency at the very least.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "It would be even better if the Collection Agency would give notice of validation at least 5 days before any attempt is made to Collect.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "This notice would give the Consumer a narrow window to contact the Creditor directly to satisfy a debt that may be outstanding or to inquire about the details of the alleged debt before making a good faith payment to the Collection Agency.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "The rules of Evidence Judicial Procedure should be horned during the validation process.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "With out meeting some measure of the burden of proof all functions of Debt Collection is simply a burden to the Tax Payer,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "any proceedings with out court worthy documentation would be frivolous.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "If Custody of the debt is transfered form a Creditor to and Collection Agency the Contract must be available for the Consumer or Custody of the debt by the Collection Agency should be invalidated.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "policy", "text": "Privacy should be respected.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "fact", "text": "When it come to mortgage debt; Upon the issuance of a mortgage form a bank the bottom line banks holding do not decrease.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "In essence The bank has written new currency (guaranteed by the future payment of the Property taxes, and other Taxes placed on the individual Citizens of the United States of America backed by there Social Security numbers and property deeds) in to existence.", "reasons": ["8"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "fact", "text": "Essentially the Borrower is giving the full amount of the mortgage plus interest to the mortgage lender.", "reasons": ["9"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "policy", "text": "If the FDIC truly backs Lenders, The lender should maintain the documentation of the agreed debt and a Default should be handled by the FDIC.", "reasons": ["12"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "value", "text": "Outsourcing to a Collection Agency can compromises the custody of the debt and encourages harassment of the consumer by a 3rd party.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "value", "text": "May Fraud be Minimal and Prosperity be Abundant.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1062", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "I also don't think that they should be able to call on Sundays.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "I understand that weekends are probably a good time to call people,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "but I think that weekend calling should be restricted to less hours (like maybe noon - 5pm) and only on Saturdays.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "No Sunday phone calls.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1296", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "Additionally, as loans are set up on varied systems and they fall in to collections for calls to be made ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "a break-out of phone types should be part of the \"Solutions\" .", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Example Home designated area, work designated area and Mobile-cell as well.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Three separate 'Solutions\" therefore giving a increased likelyhood of calls to be within what the statue requires.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1368", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "I don't believe that debt tolling should be legal.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "For instance, I had a medical crisis while living in Illinois for college.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "Despite having insurance, I still ended up deeply in debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "I attempted to work with the debt collectors, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "but I just couldn't keep up due to the massive amounts.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "I moved back to Wisconsin where I'm from.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "The debt has since become time-barred in Wisconsin due to the statute of limitations.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "It's not on my credit report", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "fact", "text": "and I can't be sued for it here.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "However, should I ever wish to return to Illinois again, it's like I never left and I can be raked over the coals by debt collectors all over again, including being sued.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "This doesn't make any sense.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "fact", "text": "Either I get sued or I don't.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "testimony", "text": "It's been over 10 years, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "value", "text": "and it's not like I skipped the country and \"hid\" from them.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "value", "text": "I'd like to return to Illinois, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 15, "type": "value", "text": "but doing so would kill my credit.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 16, "type": "testimony", "text": "They had 10 years to sue me.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 17, "type": "value", "text": "Isn't that enough?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 18, "type": "value", "text": "This is unfair ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 19, "type": "policy", "text": "and I believe the issue of debt tolling should be explored.", "reasons": ["18", "20"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 20, "type": "value", "text": "It's just not right.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "674", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I often get robo calls about family members debt, sometimes 3 or 4 a day, usually for family members that I haven't spoken to for decades.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "I am not sure how they get my phone no.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "as it is unlisted and I am sure the family members don't have it.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "852", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "Someone who lived at my address, more than 30 years ago had a debt with Household Finance.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "We get letters that we return \"Addressee Unknown\" and phone calls.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "Finally I called one number back and told them that the person they looked for wasn't there.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "That law firm stopped robo-calling ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "but a few months later a new one started up.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "Records should convey when debts are sold from collection agency to collection agency.", "reasons": ["0_3", "6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "Why should I have to go through all that a second time?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "policy", "text": "I also think debt collectors should be prohibited from using the address to get a phone number after 2 years.", "reasons": ["9"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "testimony", "text": "This debt was more than 30 years old", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "why do they think anyone who knew here would still live there?", "reasons": ["8"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "testimony", "text": "I googled the woman's name.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "testimony", "text": "I found out on the first search that she lives about 10 miles from here.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "value", "text": "If I can find her that easily why can't a debt collector, who stands to gain something, be bothered to do a little research?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1380", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "The ACA's (debt collectors) positions on the CFPB's proposed rules is disgusting!!", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "It is laughable!", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "See for yourself America,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "reference", "text": "here it is: http://www.acainternational.org/files.aspx?p=/images/31323/aca-anpr-comments.pdf", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "422", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "The CFPB should ban workplace calls completely.", "reasons": ["1_2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "Consumers provided a home phone number when they take on the debt", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "and that should be the number they call to collect it.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "Communicating by registered/certified letter should also be the alternate method not workplace calls.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "Second Massachusetts limiting the total number of calls is a fabulous idea.", "reasons": ["6", "7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "We don't throw debtors in prison today", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "yet the ridiculous amount of abuse and scorn they must endure is totally unacceptable.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "policy", "text": "CFPB desperately needs to clean up the debt collection industry.", "reasons": ["6"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "869", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Verifying the debt by the collector is a must.", "reasons": ["1_10"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I had an instance where the bill was sent to wrong address.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "After 6 months I got a call reg the debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "They mentioned only the amount and the service provider.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "when service provider was contacted they said already it is on collection and we're not helpful.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "i asked them to send the Bill to pay it off.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "Only more calls from collector started.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "After almost 6/7 requests to the collector the bill detail was sent .", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "testimony", "text": "On verification with my bank statement I found out that the amount had been paid.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "testimony", "text": "When confronted both the collector and service provider did not bother to apologize for the mistake.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "It is a case of non verification.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1234", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Dear CFPB: I hope you will separate the comments about debt buyers from those about debt collection in general.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "This is another area where you should throw the book at collectors telling deliberate lies or misrepresentations.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "On the other hand, there are too many federal suits brought by consumers who were not misled but who allege that the least sophisticated consumer might have been misled by a letter written in good faith.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "The only ones who benefit are attorneys.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "The CFPB has power under UDAAP in addition to the FDCPA to punish liars.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "They should use it.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "Collectors, who are just lay people in most cases should not be held to a strict liability standard.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "policy", "text": "Punish bad actors but ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "policy", "text": "restore reasonableness to the act.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1260", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Collection agencies should abide by the rules and regulations surrounding HIPPA (medical), Customer Proprietary Network Information (FCC) and other statutes already in place.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "While the CRPB cannot change those statutes, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "agencies must still abide by it.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1326", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "One communication from the debt collector per week is plenty.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "On top of that, The debt collector's phone rep should have power over the autodialer in the following way.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "A consumer's number is on the screen, the report log on that number is on the screen, the most current info at the top of the screen.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "If the debt collector phone rep sees that the very last communication does is already updated (such as waiting on a job interview with a date that is still in the future), then the debt collector phone rep should have the power to prevent the auto dialer from making the call.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "Not only does this prevent unnecessary hounding of the customer, it also helps prevent abusive reactions from consumers towards the debt collector phone rep", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "because the consumer recalls their last communication and that what was discussed could not have reasonably happened yet.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "702", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "There was another debt collector that went after me a second time.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "First they placed me on their hit list trying to get me to pay the debt of a man with my last name and first initial.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "I told them that they were contacting the wrong person.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "Then, several months later, they went after me again, this time looking for a woman with my last name and first initial.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "After the second round, I send them a cease-communication letter,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "and they haven't called me again.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "865", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "E mail is good alternative", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "but majority of the time it will go to junk or spam mail ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "and the purpose not served.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Regular mail with follow up on e mail be better", "reasons": ["0_2"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1218", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "In 2010 I was sued by a debt collector for a debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "At the time I was in my final year of law school and was surprised at the amount of misinformation used by the plaintiff's attorney (e.g. claiming that no proof of assignment was necessary).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "I informed the attorney that I would need proof that this was my debt as well as proof that his client had proper assignment of the debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "He responded by threatening (via e-mail) to interfere with my Bar admission process.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "I did not believe that an unsubstantiated debt would affect my ability to sit for the bar", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "and so I stood my ground.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "He dropped the case (without prejudice) in Magistrate Court and then re-filed in State Court five months later while I was going through my Certification for Fitness process.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "As a result of his second lawsuit, the State Bar did not allow me to sit for the Bar", "reasons": ["6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "due to \"a pending lawsuit\" about debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "testimony", "text": "He eventually also dropped the lawsuit in State Court.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "testimony", "text": "He never shared proof of this purported debt nor did he ever produce proof of assignment", "reasons": ["11"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "testimony", "text": "presumably because he never had valid proof of either).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "value", "text": "Nonetheless he was effective in \"punishing\" me by interfering with my ability to sit for the Bar after graduating from law school.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "fact", "text": "this occurred in Georgia.", "reasons": null, "evidence": ["14_15"]}, {"id": 14, "type": "fact", "text": "Their rules for Bar Admission are available online at", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 15, "type": "reference", "text": "https://www.gabaradmissions.org/home", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "661", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "No robo-calls or automated dialing systems should be allowed for any profit-making or solicitation purpose. Period.", "reasons": ["2", "3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "You can call me if a tornado is coming,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "but if you want money, you have to use a person.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "And I don't see why I should pay for the call.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1323", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Consumers should be able to request calls be limited to one contact per week if they desire.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "That is a fair and honorable compromise,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "741", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "The CFPB doesn't need to craft rules to encourage non-litigation alternatives or not to sell to those who utilize litigation models.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "BillBartmann's data is suspect as to 10M lawsuits filed yearly and likely his models comparing litigation and non litigation data has not been published.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "The facts are consumers need to reach out and communicate to a lender, agency, or debt buyer rather than not communicating at all.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "Debts not repaid usually result in the debt being charged off ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "so the consumer had a minimum of 180 days to seek alternative repayment options.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "Lenders, collection agencies and debt buyers have a right to sue a legal debt just like the IRS.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "Keep in mind that judgments last longer than open credit accounts looking at statute of limitations.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "To BillBatram's comment that filing bankruptcy creates hell as far as FICO scores, consumers face that issue with non payment of debt", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "and bankruptcy is an alternative for a consumer to have a fresh start.", "reasons": ["9"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "That was the intent of the bankruptcy law and still is.", "reasons": ["10"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "Consumers with little or no hope to repay debts care more about moving forward with their lives instead of worrying about FICO SCORES.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "557", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "You may want to see an attorney specializing in FDCPA cases and take that collector to court.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Federal law might be in your favor with all the validation requests ignored.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1299", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "There should be clear guidelines on what constitutes \"irrelevant and frivolous\".", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "In my own experience, the CRA's consistently refused to delete trade lines not belonging to me even when I had provided documentation from the original creditor validating the debt was not mine.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "They falsely claimed they received additional information from the original creditor that superseded the documentation I had.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "When I circled back to the original creditor, I had learned the debt was sold to a junk debt buyer which leads to a separate issue.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "If the junk debt buyer is reporting to a credit reporting agency, why are they misrepresenting themselves as the original creditor.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "Junk Debt buying should be prohibited all together.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "The original creditors should know their vendors just as the law mandates they know their customers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "policy", "text": "If the vendor is violating the law on the original creditor's behalf the original creditor should hold responsibility to some extent.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1145", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Yes, I do think your restrictions on workplace calls per week would be helpful,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "but I do not see any information requiring details on the content of Robo-Calls. ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "For example, the calls I referred to earlier included robo-calls telling me that I had \"messages\" waiting for me in my Bayview Account, and to access these messages, I needed to call a special phone number.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Well, this was a bunch of baloney", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "it was just a recording wanting to know where I had sent my mortgage payment", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "I had not set up an electronic deposit yet, like they wanted,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "so they assumed I was skipping a payment).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "I believe those robo-calls were fraudulent and misleading,", "reasons": ["8", "9"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "testimony", "text": "particularly since I was never late on any payments, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "testimony", "text": "and I never had any \"message\" waiting for me. Just a robotic collection message.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "testimony", "text": "I received three of these messages", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "testimony", "text": "and they are still saved in my cell phone voice mail.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "383", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Debt collectors should not be allowed to alter their caller ID information.", "reasons": ["1_2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "They call misrepresenting themselves as \"Process Servers\" inquiring information about another person's debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "This prevents the consumer from reporting the debt collector for violating consumer protection laws", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "because a false identify was used.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "396", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "The Pro Publica piece on one \"installment\" loan lender has plenty of examples of harassment that goes over the line that is not covered by this language", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Truly dreadful conduct.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "reference", "text": "http://www.propublica.org/article/installment-loans-world-finance", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "487", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "If a collector is calling from a different number than the one they are displaying on Called ID, that should be not allowed.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "Does not allow the consumer to block those calls since the number displayed is not the one actually calling.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1280", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I was harassed for months by a collector who used robo-calls 5 and 6 times a day and blocked its caller ID, for what turned out to be five different debts, none of which were mine.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "Robo-calls were not answered;", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "if I picked up, nobody was there, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "and no messages were ever left.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "The blocked caller ID was \"1 Unavailable,\" which is designed to outfox call-blocking from the recipient's end, and makes it impossible to identify the caller using reverse number lookups and the like.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "One day I picked up ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "and finally there was someone on the other end, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "so I was able to figure out who was calling, ", "reasons": ["6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "although they were very reluctant to say who they were.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "testimony", "text": "I then looked them up on the internet and got a phone number for them.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "testimony", "text": "I repeatedly stated I was not the person they were looking for, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "testimony", "text": "but they refused to stop calling.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "testimony", "text": "I finally got an attorney ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "testimony", "text": "and after months of the attorney bickering with them, I did get a small money settlement.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "testimony", "text": "This was occurring when I was getting chemotherapy treatment for cancer and was very ill.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 15, "type": "value", "text": "My life was hell for months because of these practices.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 16, "type": "policy", "text": "Collectors should be prohibited from concealing either their identity or their call-back numbers.", "reasons": ["15"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 17, "type": "testimony", "text": "This happened ", "reasons": ["18"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 18, "type": "testimony", "text": "because I had moved and was assigned a new number that evidently had belonged to a number of individuals who had outstanding debts.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 19, "type": "value", "text": "I was afraid to change my number again ", "reasons": ["20"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 20, "type": "value", "text": "because it would just usher in a new batch of collectors.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 21, "type": "policy", "text": "There should also be much, much, much stiffer monetary penalties for violations.", "reasons": ["23"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 22, "type": "fact", "text": "The guilty party in the above scenario was a national collection agency with huge annual revenues; ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 23, "type": "testimony", "text": "the piddly amount I was eventually paid was to them a tiny fraction of one cent compared to their annual revenues.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 24, "type": "testimony", "text": "I just happen to be an attorney myself, and ran their name on Pacer--", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 25, "type": "testimony", "text": "they had been sued over and over in state and federal court and had actually paid million dollar fines to state attorneys general--also just a small cost of doing business for them compared to their enormous annual revenues.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 26, "type": "policy", "text": "We need much, much stiffer penalties.", "reasons": ["23", "25"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 27, "type": "value", "text": "These people are cyber bullies with absolutely no scruples.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 28, "type": "policy", "text": "At the very least they should be required to identify themselves on caller i.d. with a legitimate callback number, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 29, "type": "policy", "text": "and robo-calls should be made illegal.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "672", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I would like something that addresses the amount of times a debt collector can contact someone other than the debtor.", "reasons": ["1_3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "My husband's exwife has several debts", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "and we are sometimes contacted several times a day and often at night to find out if we are in contact with her", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "they have been divorced 36 years", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "225", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "CA has already made great strides as to debt buyers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "This should be the rule for all collectors: that when they file, they must produce properly authenticated backing for the debt sued upon.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "611", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "If I am paying for the minutes on my phone, which I do, then I should be able to chose who's call I do and do not want to answer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "When it comes up 'unknown\", how do I know it's a Collection Agency, a telemarketer trying to sell me vacation homes, cruse lines trying to sell me a cruse, someone wanting to offer me a better mortgage rate, ect...", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "Every call I answer deducts time from my minutes ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "and that is NOT fair to me.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "I now block ALL \"unknown, withheld & private\" calls.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "If they truly are legidimate and want to talk to me, press 1 to unblock, just like I have to.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1261", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Collection Calls and Dunning notices (via letter or email) should include a unique Collection ID.", "reasons": ["2", "3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "This would be listed in credit reports for the purposes of tracking ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "and consumers would be able to enter into a online database provided by the CRPB with the type of violation or issue.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "This would also make it easier for the CRPB to look up disputes and determine if there's an actual issue.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1118", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Unless and until debt collection practices have greater transparency for consumers there will be abuses and misunderstandings regarding legal liability.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "It's too much a pat answer to say consumers should seek legal advice.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "Collectors should be required to say with a certain level of supported certainty whether the debt is valid or not.", "reasons": ["1", "3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "Collectors should not be allowed to rely merely on a borrower's \"moral obligation\" to repay the debt.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "Financially disadvantaged, naive, and gullible consumers, and specifically those individuals on fixed, limited incomes, i.e., older Americans, ESL citizens, etc. are especially vulnerable.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "525", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "AT & T is notorious for setting up new accounts that don't have an official phone number attached.", "reasons": null, "evidence": ["1_7"]}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I was put in the situation of having an 800 number that AT & T customer service reps could not find in their system.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "I had no way to cancel it!", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "Eventually the false 100 dollar debt went to a debt collector.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "I respectfully explained that the debt was not valid, in a letter.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "A few months later I got a letter from a different debt collector.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "Again I wrote a letter.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "A few months later another letter over the same faux debt from a third debt collector.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "854", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "When we did it, it was agreed that any 3rd party communication outside SOL at any point was a potential violation of the FDCPA.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "Since 3rd party debt collectors are required to be truthful at all times,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "they cannot say 'we are attempting to collect a debt' if they are time-barred from collecting the debt.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "We were the meanest, nastiest, most aggressive in the multi-state area at that time,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "and this was the stance.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "Suggestion is clarify that time-barred debts are time-barred for the 3rd party as well, and cannot be collected, attempted to be collected, or bought/sold.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1242", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I am in the same situation as From_ill_annoy.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have been denied credit and loans as a result of these adverse actions which have impacted both my personal and professional life.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "717", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Once companies have sold the debt to a collection agency they do not help resolve it in any way", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "and the collection agency is only interested in getting money not whether the debt is real or there were some mitigating circumstances.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1141", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "I am dealing with a debt collection company who is also a mortgage company.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "They are having issues separating the two types of services.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "They are also having an incredible amount of IT (web) problems.", "reasons": null, "evidence": ["3", "4"]}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "Their website is down, or only their staff can see it, or they cannot upload my account information, etc.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "Other IT issues include their System, which \"tells them\" it has mailed me documents, but apparently does not really do it.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "My point is, I am able to capture a lot of this using ScreenShots and electronic communication, providing a very detailed log.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have sent my screenshots of the errors I saw on my account screen to their IT staff,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "and it may have helped resolve their website issues a few weeks later.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "I would highly recommend the use of electronic media as a formal way to communicate on both ends.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "463", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "If the consumer requests you do not call someone, do not call.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "This also leads into collector games, such as calling mother/father. brother, sister with sam elast name saying you thought it was their spouse and you were calling about an account...", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "195", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "State and local court rules sometimes make default judgments much more likely.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "For example, when a person who allegedly owes a debt is told to come to court on a work day, they may be forced to choose between a default judgment and their job.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "I urge the CFPB to find practices that involve scheduling hearings at inconvenient times unfair, deceptive, and abusive, or inconsistent with 1692i.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "688", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I would like to see requirements that the consumers are required to provide written notice of any new addresses for the creditor to reach them", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "so in the event the account does go into default, the creditor has current information to attempt to contact the consumer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Many consumers move frequently, yet fail to update the creditors", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1269", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "It apprears that the debt collectors of the debt collection industry are conducting a money laundry and racketing operation by explointing and obtaining monetary from comsumers for products that they don't sell to them or services that they don't provide to consumers with no inital purchase contract with consumers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "It appears that debt collectors are obtaining monetary from consumers where they don't have licenses to sell products to consumers or provide services to consumers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "It appears that debt collectors are costing companies money when companies are trying to recover their loses when they miss payments from their customers for the products that they sell to their customers or the services that they provide to their customers with alegal purchase contracts.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "It seems that debt collector are relying on companies' money and on consumers' money for an income when they are not initially involved in the a company sale of products to consumers or in the distributing of a company of services to a consumers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1132", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "New rules should allow consumers to resolve, discuss, or negotiate the matter strictly with the creditor.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "In other words, consumers should be told that they can refuse to speak to debt collectors about their account(s).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "439", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "This is a problem that needs to be corrected.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "In this case, the line of credit is negatively affecting your credit a multiple of times even though it is one line.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "578", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "If there already isn't a law or rule at the fed level for when what happens to time barred debts when a debtor leaves the purview of one states SOL and now resides in another states SOL, there needs to be.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "It should be clear that if a debtor changes states, which SOL should come into play.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1097", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "The problem is not with a form letter of dispute.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "The problem is that these websites and unreasonable letters lead unsophisticated debtors to believe that a creditor has to provide extraordinary proof that simply is not required.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "'stopwithspoofedcallerID' (if that IS your real name) is correct that no legitimate dispute should be ignored, regardless of the form, but nor should debtors be allowed to abuse the system by repeatedly asking for proofs that are not required.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "776", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "what kind of consumer contacts do debt collectors... disputing the debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "That presumes they actually follow the law and do a validation investigation.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "That is wrong,", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "they do not.", "reasons": ["4_12"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "I sent a letter to a company claiming I owed a debt", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "and I was clear I was disputing the debt. A clear, declaratory sentence.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "I mailed it to the address listed.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "There was NO PERSON who signed this letter to me.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "testimony", "text": "I had to send it to To Whom It Concerned.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "But it was clear I was disputing the debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "testimony", "text": "I did so within two weeks, well within the 30 days.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "testimony", "text": "Yet they did nothing but wait 30 days and send me a letter saying \"here is the info you requested.\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "testimony", "text": "It contained nothing I recognized.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "value", "text": "You are presuming they are actually validating.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "value", "text": "This is the biggest mistake.", "reasons": ["15"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 15, "type": "value", "text": "They do none of that.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 16, "type": "value", "text": "Any rule that defines what qualifies as a dispute would help. The clearer, the better.", "reasons": ["17"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 17, "type": "value", "text": "The vagueness now has led to abuses. Such as \"frivolous and irrelevant\" disputes.", "reasons": ["18"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 18, "type": "value", "text": "That is a license to abuse consumers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "494", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "I agree both party's should be aware if any recording is going on.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "It is fair for both sides", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1377", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "Some of us find ourselves on the receiving end of daily (or more frequent) robo calls ", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "because we have common last names.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "And I do think that the debt collectors who have called me would very much like me to pay the debt even though it isn't mine.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "708", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "The FDCPA needs to be brought into current times.", "reasons": ["1", "2", "3", "4", "5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "It is more efficient and effective for collectors for sure.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "It is the preferred method of communication for consumers without a doubt.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Most would certainly rather get an email or text, rather than a phone call.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "Regular mail is inefficient and becoming more expensive every year and often ignored.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "It benefits everyone to update to allow using modern technology to communicate with each other.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "Social networking is can should be used for locating only.", "reasons": ["7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "I don't believe that communications through social networking is in the best interest for any of the parties involved.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1019", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "Debt Neutrality Petition, you have made a lot of arguments in this thread about \"involuntary\" defaulters.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "However, the law doesn't make that distinction.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Financial hardship is not a defense to someone's failure to repay a debt that he or she promised to", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "803", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "What a great idea -- record them.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Reading these comments, there are so many examples of abuse, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "it seems like this Consumer Protection agency ought to have gotten the message thus far: the phones are used to harass.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "The only way to get this to stop is to put some teeth into the laws through civil fines,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "not put the onus on the consumer to have to sue.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1092", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I had a debt collector tell me they told me that if I'd make a payment right then they'd make a payment plan.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "This was an Amercian Express collector.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "Once I made the payment they said they're supervisor would have to approve it and they weren't there. But that she would call back at 7pm MST to make the arrangement.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "Needless to say no one called back", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "and American Express would not make arrangements with me ", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "because they said I was able to pay that amount so I shouldn't need arrangements.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "I was so dumbfounded by the collection practices of American Express.", "reasons": ["0_4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "It was from their internal collections department.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1206", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "Yes, that just happened to me today,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "someone called trying to locate a friend saying they were a \"courier service.\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "208", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I received a bill from an attorneys office regarding a bill I did not think that was mine.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I sent a certified return receipt request for validation but never received a response.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "So I sent a 2nd certified return receipt - request for validation and again never received a response.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "The attorneys office filed a civil suit and took me to court.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "I explained this to the judge and gave proof.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "The proof I submitted into the court file were copies of request of validation, the USPS certified letter statement's and request verification receipt statement's.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "This was all ignored by the judge ", "reasons": ["7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "because I was pro se and did not know Washington state law.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "testimony", "text": "I had made the request prior to this case being filed.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "testimony", "text": "Later it was explained to me by an attorney that the local county civil courts do not enforce federal laws, only state laws and in state court a request for validation is not recognized.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "testimony", "text": "I also requested proof of licensing which I did not receive ", "reasons": ["11"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "testimony", "text": "because the plaintiff was and currently is not a licensed in Washington state as a debt collection agency ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "testimony", "text": "- they are attorneys.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "testimony", "text": "The plaintiff won their case", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "testimony", "text": "and I owed a debt that was not mine.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 15, "type": "value", "text": "I ask you, where is the fairness in this?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 16, "type": "policy", "text": "What needs to occur is the laws need to be made clear for both the lay person and the judicial system.", "reasons": ["15"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1151", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "I also wanted to add that because debt collectors know they can hire robo service companies to false service,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "they aren't going to negotiate in good faith.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Just as appalling for me was the judge agreeing that the one service I challenged was a false service, but allowing the case to go forward anyways.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Sure, people can lie and say they were not served when they were served,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "but the very day I was in court contesting the service, a person who spoke before me made the comment that they found their service document on their door step when they got home.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "This means the servicers are lying in court documents,", "reasons": null, "evidence": ["4"]}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "and nobody seems to care.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "I still want redress on these two cases,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "and I want to be able to file an errors and omissions claim with both debt collectors insurance company for lying on court documents.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "And if it is not a law, then isn't it time that debt collection companies carry errors and omissions insurance?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "386", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "As a Director for Collections now for Kennedy Space Center Federal Credit Union, which is over 500 Million in asset size I try as I have for prior union to file suit closest to the Consumers current address.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "One method is to assign over to an attorney within the current residence-venue of the Consumer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "In legal terms we attempt to get service when filing a suit out of state,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "its method is called obtaining if possible a Alien Juddgement outside from the County and or State the contract/note was originally signed.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "There are states in the Union that do note accept foreighn judgments.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "So recording a judgement obtained for example in Floirda and rerecorded in another State may not be possible.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1032", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Breaking a promise to pay isn't the same as breaking the law.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "We can't keep comparing criminal law to civil law ", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "because it's just not the same.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "But the item that's missing here is the legitimacy of interest.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "Forget about big banks for a minute, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "and think about borrowing money from a friend or neighbor.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "When you keep money that is rightfully owed to someone else, you damage him,", "reasons": ["7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "fact", "text": "because he doesn't have that money, which he could be investing (to increase it) or spending (to improve his quality of life).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "That's one of the reasons that interest exists", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "to compensate someone for the loss of their money for a portion of time until it gets repaid.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "fact", "text": "I'm not saying interest rates aren't excessive", "reasons": ["11"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "they certainly are", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "value", "text": "unfortunately, that's a separate issue.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "value", "text": "But suspending interest all together and allowing a debtor to freeze the amount of his debt indefinitely, because he borrowed more than he could pay back and didn't plan for unexpected expenses.... I don't know anyone who would loan money under those terms, except for maybe Mom and Dad.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "390", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "Most of the consumer debt I see if coming from debt buyers and the consumer doesn't recognize the name or the amount.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "Many of these are beyond the statute of limitations to file suit ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "but suit is filed anyway.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "Many consumers don't know to file an answer is court ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "and a default judgment is entered.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "The information you suggest would help a lot in letting consumers know what this debt is.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "I would include the trail of ownership of the debt", "reasons": ["7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "as there could be intermediary owners between the original creditor and final collector.", "reasons": ["8"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "fact", "text": "Debts are sold and resold.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "It would also help to have some documentation of the specific debt having been sold", "reasons": ["10", "11_12"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "so the consumer can verify the current ownership of the debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "fact", "text": "Currently, all they get in response to a validation request is \"we checked and you owe it\".", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "testimony", "text": "Our firm asks for specific documents related to the claimed debt and the response we get is \"the courts say we don't have to provide any documents...go fish\".", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "392", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "The majority of the collection disputes I help my clients with are never validated with documentation.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "The CRA simply sends a letter stating that the debt was verified ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "although the dispute letter specifically asked for documentation.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1135", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "When creditor or servicing company doesn't \"credit\" a payment after receiving it and then getter further proof but still puts the victim in arrears or foreclosure, there should be fines regardless of whether it is a \"mistake\" or \"criminal act.\"", "reasons": ["3", "5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "A grace period can be allowed", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "but after that slap on the fines. and keep them coming every week they don't correct their problem.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Basically by not crediting payment they are stealing that payment.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "This should apply to any \"mistakes\" or unethical practices such as deliberately or \"mistakenly\" changing around escrow, interest, principal, late fees, insurance and so forth to the profit of the collector.", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "Heavy fines will take away the profit motive and such \"mistakes\" and unethical practices will greatly decrease.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "905", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "Keep in mind, a cease and desist letter does not stop a debt collector from attempting to collect a debt,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "it only stops the debt collector from communicating with the consumer via whatever method the consumer requests the contact to stop.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "This does not mean a consumer no longer owes a debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "I do agree with the fact that a debt collector must notify the creditor of disputes.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "As a matter of fact, legitimate debt collectors do this on a regular basis.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "As a debt collector typically does not own the debt,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "they're unable to control what a creditor does with that information,", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "all they are currently able to do is implement internal controls that protect the consumer and the agency.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "policy", "text": "In my opinion, a legitimate dispute should be defined ", "reasons": ["9"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "fact", "text": "as currently, a consumer solely mentioning the word dispute requires action on an account.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "policy", "text": "I believe some sort of requirement should be imposed as to WHY an account is being disputed and some sort of evidence be provided to support the claim.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "513", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have no personal experiences with debt to speak of, only my experiences working with victims of identity theft who have fraudulent debts; which is a horse of a different color.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "Consumers are not educated about how debt collection and revival works.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "The issue in the end isn't the mechanics, or if they can request the debt not be reported.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "The issue is that, the way things stand now, it is not clear how repaying a debt will improve their score.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "It is not clear that they can ask for the collector not to report the debt payment if the debt is older than seven years.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "Consumers are confused and have these inaccurate perceptions because things are not clear.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "Again, it is the perception which concerns me - it would benefit both creditors and consumers if it was plain and clear, in language the average consumer could understand, that paying off a debt is a good thing.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1300", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I am all for consumers right protection", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "but when you see CFPB, FDCPA and other law they are all to make it difficult for collection agencies to do their honest job.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "But there is never a talk about consumers responsibilities.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "I agree that some collection agencies are aggressive.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "but I think a good honest collection agencies also need their rights to do honest work.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "358", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "There should be a federal rule prohibiting collectors from reporting information to a CRA during the 30-day window.", "reasons": ["1_3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "There are automated processes in place with many collectors where they will generate 4 collection letters at one time, including the one where they tell you that they have reported you to a CRA.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "And then they will mail all those to letters (all dated on the same day) to you at the same time.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "And this is done without any debt verification whatsoever.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "721", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I believe most default judgments occur for one reason: the consumers know they owe the debt and see no reason to prolong the situation.", "reasons": ["1_3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "Many consumers will call us and make payment arrangements after being served.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "We advise them they have the opportunity to be heard in court but most decline.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "They simply want to resolve the debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "533", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "It is against the law to call cell phones.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "And to send out texts.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "And no matter how much the debt collection lobbyists try to change the law, it won't work.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1051", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Your point about the overshadowing is well taken.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "My comments are based upon suggested changes to the debt collection process.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "You are correct,", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "if the FDCPA remained the way it is currently it may be considered a violation.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "The FDCPA allegedly is geared to the \"least sophisticated individual\".", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "However, I currently speak to many people that are not able to properly respond to a debt validation (even when they have a credible dispute).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "I am currently dealing with a 72-year old woman whose son \"stole\" her identity.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "He was convicted of fraud and deported for other credit cards that he took out in her name.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "testimony", "text": "She received a dunning notice and now is being sued on another card that she was not even aware of.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "Our experiences are just different.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "I once felt the same way as you when I was in commercial debt collection.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "I truly appreciate your response", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "value", "text": "but you and I will have to disagree that \"he or she should be able to articulate that dispute\".", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "value", "text": "I enjoyed reading your well thought out response and look forward to the continued debate.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
